\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could we start with your name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Mrs - Lucy McLelland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And your address here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Flat 6, All Saints House, All {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Saints Road{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}, W.ll. W.ll. 1HG.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And can you remember the year of your marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1926}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Day}{\xmlattrvalue 16}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 2}}}February the sixteenth, 1926{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember the year of your birth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname date}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Year}{\xmlattrvalue 1900}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Day}{\xmlattrvalue 10}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Month}{\xmlattrvalue 1}}}January the tenth, 1900{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was born in - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname address}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname Street}}Thames Street{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Greenwich{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that a house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Little - little house, just by the Haven. It used to be a Haven where the - boats, or the barges as you would call them, used to come up to the wharf along the Thames,
 and they used to bring - all the hay, and put it into this big building. Alongside the Thames.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it noisy there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not very noisy. But - I do remember - a big fire there was - at the hay wharf caught fire. And I remember the firemen - carr
ying me out - on his shoulder - into - Horsefeery Road as - and there was all the - what you call 'em - water pipes, all up and down the street. You just - you had - really had a job to get along. I always remember that. But I think my age was three. Befo
re -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long did you live in the house in Thames Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we must have been there about six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And then you moved to where?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we moved then up to - Dutton Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's at Blackheath. Up on the hi
ll near the Greenway. What they call the Green Man, going over to Blackheath. And I was there at school for about - four or five years. And then we came back to Greenwich again. Because it was too far out for me father. Being he was working - on the river
.
 And then - his work, he could only work - when the tide was up, because he was a waterman. He worked - driving - the tug for the coal to go up and down the river - into the gas company. The Liversey. The - boat was called, but - and also the gas company 
was - was - named after - Liversey. He was the - founder of the gas company.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So your father only worked when the tide was right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he couldn't work when the time was out. He had to work when the tide - they worked with the tides.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Sometimes they had to work at night did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. Oh yes, he was working all hours. He wasn't like - could say - I'll be out at nine and back again at six or seven. He only worked when the tide was on. So that's how he had to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So he wouldn't have any regular times for being at home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no, no, no, we never - knew when he was going to be in on out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many hours a day did he have to work, twelve hours a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, quite. Quite. Yes. And then - there's some da
ys when he was at - laying at the moorings as they used to call it, this was here at Stepney - along the Thames, and - we would be able to take his dinner to him. So we used to take his dinner in two plates tied up with a red - spotted handkerchief. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would be inside the plates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - he'd have a bit of meat - or a chop and greens and potatoes. And sometimes he would - he used to come in a rowing boat to get it, to the steps, you know, by the - bank, and then he used to r
ow back. And we used to run back home was a good twenty minutes - from Greenwich, all along the - we passed the Naval College, used to go right along there, into Greenwich, East Greenwich and there we used to get to where his moorings was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time of day would that be when you took him his dinner?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well that would be when he was - there at two o'clock, and was able, you know, he couldn't - just enough water - to bring - the little rowing boat over - to the steps. And we used to go down these wo
oden steps and give him his dinner and he'd row back to his - tug again. And we'd go off. 'Cos we had to get to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did a lot of other children do that for their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - we never did meet them you see, it was just that was his job you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was wondering whether the whole Thames was alive with children taking dinner to their dads.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no. No, it was just ones - used to go there you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember what was the name of the place you went to to be nearer the river, was it Bridge Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Bridge Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would you be living in 1911 then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was in Bridge Street. Just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In 1911?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Just there by the Grit Bridge, and the bridge used to go up - when the tide was in, and 
let all the - big ships - that used to come along, and go through to the - to get to the other side. And then they'd go right out, round - into the Thames.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not many ships use it now do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, you don't see the ships like there used to be them
 days, 'cos they used to work those days. A lot of water work used to be done then. But now I don't think there's much - 'cos I think the gas company - has closed down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What number was it in Bridge Street that you lived at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 123. But I'm sorry to say - the house is - knocked down. I think they've taken it over as offices.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's what happening all over that area of London at the moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I'm sorry, but I did - I was there - two years ago. I was taken through - Greenwich, with the co
ntact people, and - to my astonishment I find the house is gone.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why did you leave your Thames Street house originally to move to Dutton Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that was 'cos of the fire you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The fire was actually?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. It - all - our 
- our house - backed onto the wharf, so therefore it was all red and - got scorched and that, and another thing - there was more children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You wanted more room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We had to have more room you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many rooms were there in the house in Thames Street then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about Dutton Street, how many were in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, we had the basement, and also - the next floor, the first floor, because - there was more children then you see, there was about - three - in Thames St
reet, then we had about six - when we got to Dutton Street, the time we - were there and left. Then we come back to Greenwich - to Bridge Street, and there there was - fourteen altogether, but only thirteen of us lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you were the second eldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How much older than you was the older sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She was two years. We were all - steps and stairs. There was about eighteen months between us all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And how many brothers were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was - seven boys. And six girls. 
The seven boys are living now. But the six girls, there's only four. The other two - have died with cancer. This last six years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd all be quite young still wouldn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Before the first world war you'd all be living together in the same house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many rooms did you have in the other house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
In Bridge Street? Well we had - four rooms, and a scullery. And there we used to have the copper. And bring the tin bath in for a bath and - used t
o have to wait - you know, 'til there was - one had had a bath and then the other one - and that's how we did it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When would bath}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 night be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh it was any time. Sometimes Sunday morning, sometimes Saturday night. All depends what mother or f
ather was doing. You see. And when we had our food, our meals, we used to have a relay. Yes. Because we couldn't all sit round the table. Some would sit at - the machine. You know, being a table machine, we'd - sit there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What do you - mean by a table machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, the old fashioned machines, they had a table, and the machines weren't so big as they are - as - as they are now you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You mean the cooker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, sewing machine. The sewing machine. So - that's what we used to do. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many would sit round the machine at one go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well we had one each side you see, and then - the rest would be at the table, the baby would be in the high chair, and the other baby would be on me mother's lap. And Sunday morning - we used to lay in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you all sleep, did you share rooms or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - well - for sleeping - the girls slept upstairs. We had - two beds, one - a full sized bed. There'd be about four in that one. And then we had two singles, in the back room. And
 me brothers, they would sleep downstairs, about three boys. And then the babies, about two or three of them - would sleep in me mother's room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you had three rooms really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, they were all bedrooms. There was no sitting rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No reception rooms or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, nothing of that, no. It was all - living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I don't know how old he was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How old was he when he died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he died at - 19 - 6 - between 1966 - and 1967, that would be with the war wouldn't it. With the second world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 '67 or '47?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 '47 would it be. '47 was the second - I get mixed up with the first world war. '47. 1947.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember how old he was then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he was - sixty-three - bless him. Yes. Sixty-three. See with the hard work and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So he'd be about twenty-three when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he the same age as your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No - I - yes, she would - he would be 'co
s me mother was - seventy-five and she didn't - die 'til she was - in 1957, so they would be about the same age. But of course - I wouldn't like to tell you how me father - he fretted really, he could have lived longer, but you see that terrible strike - 
in 1920 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What strike was this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The big strike they had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The general strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. In 1920. The - or was it '26, 1926 wasn't it. Yes, 1926. Well - what happened there was - me father was - and his mates - they came to my father being th
at he - the tide wasn't up you see to go to work, but one of the men came to my - knocked at the house and said, it's no good, Alf, going in. They're - out on strike. So therefore, my father didn't get up and go down to see. So when he got there - they - 
they sacked him. And he would have been on the retired pension then. They sacked him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did he do after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he had to take any job. And - and being a conscientious man - he - he fretted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember him ever being out of work before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Never been out of work before. That's what did it. It killed him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he ever have any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, nothing. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Greenwich. Greenwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She come from Catford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's just a few miles away isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Lew - Lewisham way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did she do before she got married, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I should say she was in service. Never heard of her speak of her - what she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did she do any work after she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, she had too many children. She had too many children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of job did he do after the general strike?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The same sort of thing. Taking - the tug up the river, you know. B
ut it was for another company and he wasn't happy. So - with the worry I suppose that brought the cancer on. - And he died in Greenwich hospital - the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  Seaman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 '}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s hospital.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was 1947 you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said you lived in these houses, did you have any relatives or lodgers with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no, there was our own small houses, our own - and the rent was only seven and four a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did the landlord live? Was he a local man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was a local landlord. Yes. Used to come every week - and take the rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of bloke was he then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Very nice man, very nice. Very nice man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember whether your relatives lived nearby or did they live quite a way away? Did you have many sort of relatives in the area?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh they lived in the area, and they're still living there. All his brothers and sisters and - grandfather and - and - uncles. They're all born Greenwich people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have much to do with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes. Used to go up - Sunday morning, 
me father used to get us all ready and - go and see me father's - well my grandmother as she was, then father's mother and - and - his father. And Uncle George. And they used to give us a penny. We used to think a lot of that and - come home and - then we
'd - go to Sunday school. And have our dinner when we got back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would you have for dinner on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we - well me mother used to get a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 itch}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  bone - of beef, which was - be only about three shillings - them days. But we didn't get much meat, we had more veg.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have meat during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, yes. Well you might as well call it meat. I used to have to - and my brother and I used to get up at six o'clock in the morning and go to a shop in London High Street, called Maynards, and - we used to get }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
pennyworth of pork rinds and bones. And we used to bring that back, and me mother used to make - quite big pot of lentil soup, all the veg and that, and we used to eat the rinds and - everything else. And the bits that was on the bones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time of day would you eat that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We'd - well we'd have that for our dinner when we come home from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would be about five o'clock time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well she always managed my mother to give us a dinner. So
me days we'd have - bread and cheese. But then we'd have a hot meal at night. That was if father was home see. But when father was out - that's when we used to have the soup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd have a meal at lunchtime, what would you call the midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes - that was when we had the pork rinds and bones, the soup, or she might - get two}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pennorth of pieces. Or a pound of sausages - for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence. See the stuff was so cheap - them days we could get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time would you have breakfast in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, breakfast we only used to have a bit of bread. Bread and butter. We never - or a bit of jam you know, and a cup of tea. And then off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time did you have to be at school by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was the school nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. In Bridge Street. Called St Peters. St. Peters school, Greenwich. It was a church school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about when you were in Dutton Street, where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I went to this - here - the - what they called the Blucken school, it was
 - there used to be boys dressed - in blue coats. I've never been able to find out what it was, I'll have to go back. To Greenwich and find out what that was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, but I wasn't in the uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Which school did you prefer?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I preferred the - Bridge Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it a church school in Dutton Street as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, that was just an ordinary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not a boarding school, no. Just a - you know - ordinary school, I went ho
me every day. But as I tell you, it was too far out for me father - to get - to Greenwich you know with all these fogs, 'cos we used to have terrible fogs them days and - a job at night when he was perhaps coming home here two in the morning. It was a lon
g walk. After doing all them hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would affect his social life quite a lot wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He wouldn't be able to go out a lot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother ever go out anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, she went to mothers meetings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And they were in the Albany Institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, she used to take the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would happen there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they used to - make things and talk. And they used to have - baby competitions and that - 'cos I remember me mother
, she - she won one for having thirteen children. They called it the baker's dozen, and that was at the Albany Institute - in Bridge Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many times a week was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Once a week. And then she'd go to another - she'd go to - another meetin
g at - St Peters, what they call a mothers meeting you know, the women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
s - a church - meeting. So she got out like that sort of thing. And I think that's why us girls - we do it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So she didn't stay at home all the time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your father ever go out anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he a member of any club or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh no, no. No, he just might go to the local but not much. He might take mother out to - Friday night, if he was home, he'd go to New Cross Empire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What happened there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
And then - we used to mind the children. And then they'd get back about - ten o'clock, from the Empire. That was a variety show, and then - we used to get the jug and go across to the coffee stall - and have a jug of t
ea, and perhaps if they had - a piece of meat - bit of steak, they might cook it, cut it off the aitch bone. This was here at eleven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would only be now and again you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - well - yes, it wouldn't be every week because -
 he might be working you see. But when he wasn't working he always took me mother - to the Empire, as an outing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have many relatives coming to see you, you say you went out to see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we used to have me Aunt Daise, and me Uncle
 Harry. Used to come and play the piano, and me Uncle Herbert, he used to play the piano. 'Cos we had a piano.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother or father play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, unfortunate, and - but it was - me sister - me older sister, she went to piano lessons, and that was sixpence for half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have sort of musical evenings with your uncles and aunts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Ah when he came yes, they used to come Saturday afternoons, and they used to play. We used to look forward to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would they sing or play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - Nelly Dean, or - you know - the Old Rusty Mill by the Bridge, and - what was these other - all these other old songs you know.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have anything like music halls in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes - there was a music hall th
at - that - just a public house - as you went up the Greenwich - Royal Hill there was a pub - there, a public house, and then there was a music}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hall there. But I forget the name of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go along there? Would your parents ever go along to that or did you ever go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we used to go to that, we used to go to that for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence. Up in the gods - as we used to call it, and that was in the - early evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that once a week you went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 YES? Once a week, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there cinemas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, there was cinemas but - we didn't go much to those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How about concerts or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we didn't go to many of those, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have funfairs or circuses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we - there was funfairs, plenty when - on Blackheath. And that was here when it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  Easter}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
time, and - August - Bank Holiday. Oh it was a great big fair then, Blackheath fair - it was well noted for it. Used to - mother used to take us, and we used to get - go on the roundabout for
 a penny a piece. Yes. Oh yes. Used to have a - used to go through Greenwich Park, which see wasn't far away from where we were - living. And that was a grand park, we lived in the park. Where I spent all my days for - well, nearly, in the park with the c
hildren. 'Cos when I came home from school there was about three or four children - all in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 perambulator}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 waiting for me to take them up to the park. Used to have a - a bottle of cold tea you know, and some bread and butter and we'd thought that was great
. Then come home about seven. So we used to have a grand time. And we had the deer running through the park that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Very rural really wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes, because there is - I don't know if the place is still there but there were - is a pa
th - just up there by the observatory, where Queen Elizabeth - used to bath. They show you the - open place, and the steps - where she used to go down - to get into the bath. And then there's a tree there - where - King Charles - he used to hide.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said you played in the park, did you have anywhere else you used to play, did you have a garden or anything like that in Bridge Street?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - oh yes, there was a nice garden at the back. But - we - well it was better for mother to take the youngsters
 into the park you see. It was - give her a little - a little time to herself to do the housework and - washing and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you do the washing at home or did you send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, washing at home. We had the old mangle. Oh yes, it was all done and the copper was always lit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother have anybody in to help clean the house or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. Nothing. She did it all herself. Bar the help of us children, us girls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would you do to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well we used to have to come home and - from school, and - get - clean the windows, and do the bedrooms out. And perhaps - scrub the scullery out. And there was always plenty of washing up to do. But - my older sister used to do that, and I used to be
 the one to take the children out - to the park. Oh we was never allowed to - go out and play on our own or anything like that. It was always - the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you play much with the neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What the neighbours children? Oh yes, we 
used to play - used to have a shuttlecock, and we used to bounce it up and down, and say Mrs Mason, broke our basin. How much did it cost? Penny, tuppence, three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence and four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence - and so on 'til the shuttlecock fell on the ground. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What other kind of things did you play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we used to play - marbles. And then we used to play what they called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 
\endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  alley}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
gobs. That was a - a little - china ball - and three gobs as we used to call it. Three little square pieces of - chalk, and we used to thr
ow the - bounce the - alley, as we called it, the little - china ball, and try and catch as many gobs as we could. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go on any Sunday school outings or anything like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Only a fortnight. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So it was quite a rushed decision to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. And then - he - he stayed at me mother's. They put him up. Yes. And we were - got married at the - register office in - Church Street - East Greenwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did his parents come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 His parents were Belfast. Yes. And they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they come over for the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They - no, no, they were dead, I never saw them. I never met his side, no. Well I did meet his side, I met his cousin. And his neice.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you meet at the wedding or later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Lat
er we met them. And that was at - well - after we got married we got a position - to - you know, go as butler and cook. And our first position was Agatha Christie, at Sunningdale. And - she was very interesting you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was hers a sort of smallish house compared to the Rutlands and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, and that's why - we was bored - and we didn't get on very well - I'm sorry to say, but we only had - the gardener's wife and a girl, and yet there was a three in family. There was her, and her husband, 
Colonel Christie, and their daughter, and a secretary. And you come down to wash up and do the dinners and - help your husband, 'cos he was a very proud man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is this the first time he'd done the butler's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. He'd always been - before he'd 
taken up - the Beavor Castle, he'd always been a - head fireman, in Mayfair. See, he was born in a public house, in Belfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 His father was a publican was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. But his grandfather was Doctor - and surgeons. And his cousin. His Uncle. They we
re all in Belfast. So - whether they're there now I don't know. 'Cos it's so many years ago. And you see me husband was nearly - twenty years older than me. Yes. So of course it made a lot of difference. I did take him back once - to see, you know, just b
e
fore he died, three years before he died to see if we could see anybody. But he could only show me the places - Yes, we used to go on the - in the brakes, they used to take us in brakes - them days. And they'd take us out to - Woolwich. Abbey Wood, that's
 where we used to go for the day, always to Abbey Wood.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that a park?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
The - the - it was always Abbey Wood for all of us, because the park was quite near see. Or take you on Blackheath, 'cos there's plenty of space there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many times a year would you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Once a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In the summer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And then a - a - a tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 party - for Christmas. And then on Good - Good Friday, you always had a bun. Our hot cross bun. Used to look forward to that going to - get our bun for Easter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they sort of make anything about birthdays in those days do you remember? Were birthdays special occasions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not - not in - not where - with us, 'cos we were too many. There's too many of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have cards or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we had birthday cards. But - not very many. Not very many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about Christmas, what kind of things did you do at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well at Christmas, my mother - used to get a Christmas tree, used to buy it
 at Deptford, and - we'd get one for about shilling, which you pay now - fifteen, and we used to get these little - four for a penny - sugar - you know, like a drop, or a - or a - harp, and tie it up on the Christmas tree, or a mouse or a - like animals, 
all made of sugar. And that's how we spent our Christmas amongst our own selves because we couldn't invite anybody because there was too many of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would you have for a Christmas meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we used to have - chicken, our own chickens.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had chickens in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
We kept chickens in the garden, we had our own chickens, or rabbits. Used to keep rabbits. And - that's how we - used to have our Christmas dinners. I - and a Christmas pudding, always a Christmas pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you have chickens during the year as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, because we had our own you see, and then that saved us buying meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there any tinned meat around London in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, there was corned beef. Oh yes, there was corned beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you get some of that ever?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, 'cos that was only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence a pound. Oh we very often had a lunch on that - in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could you get fish in the Thames?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they used to but we didn't get it. We used to go to the fish shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did it come from the Thames or did it come from the sea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
The sea. Come from the sea. Yes. And there was a - a - in Greenwich - the top of Bridge Street - there was a - a - vegetable market. And we used to get up in the morning and walk round tha
t and - see what we could - get, you know, the - people didn't want. Cabbage or lettuce or something like that, or apples.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would they be sort of scraps really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever grow your own vegetables in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes
. Dad always had allotment. Being in the gas company they all had a piece of ground they used to grow their own vegetables and flowers. And he was a very good - gardener. So he kept us up with beetroot and - lettuce, onions. So we didn't have very much ve
g to buy. All potatoes and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you help in the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, we used to go and - help him to weed it. Of course that was when he was off, you know, if he wasn't working. 'Cos if he - the tide was in - you know, he'd have to go to work
, but - when the - like he'd have some evenings that the tide wasn't - might have to early morning to work, two 'clock, so therefore - he used to do his gardening through the day. He'd piece of allotment you know, they all got. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother ever make her own jams or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, she used to make - jams. And she used to make - rhubarb wine. And beetroot wine, and parsnip wine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about medicines, did she do any homemade medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, we - we didn't need much, we was all - you know, pretty healthy. Used to have Galloway}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s syrup, if we were sick. Otherwise we - go to the doctor, but - it was very rare.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember being at home when one of your sisters or brothers was born? Can you remember what happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. I - I'd have to go and - fetch me grandmother, 'cos she always did the confinement, and - we used to get the water for her and that you know, but - we didn't know much about what was really going on, because - until we got older - we realized 
what was - happening, but before then it used to be - she came from France or - as if you know - was brought over in a bag.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember your mother being sick apart from that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. No. No. Nor me father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were a very healthy family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Do you ever remember thinking because you had so many brothers and sisters that it was a struggle to make ends meet for your parents in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we all had to give, there was no chance of - thinking, we had to
 give, we were - brought up that way. You see, when you became - the age, well I was lucky. See, I managed to win this scholarship - when I was fourteen and the war broke out at the same time, 1916 war, but - I did manage to get to school - called - domes
tic science, so - I went there, I should have gone 'tiol I was sixteen, but I was - able to stay - 'til I was fifteen and a half, and then I went to service.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In 1916?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, and from there I - was in service - until 1926 - when I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you work after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, yes, we worked as butler and cook. And we had the child. But it didn't work out very well. So then me husband went as a - to Whitehall - being he was a - soldier. From the first world war, but he - was able t
o get a post - in the Ministry at Whitehall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 As a butler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No, in the Ministry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did he do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A Civil Servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were a cook before you married were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. And him - we - I was a cook - to the Duke of Rut
land. Beavor Castle. That's where I ended up, but - from 19 - 16, right up to 1926 I worked in - I went to a post in - Pont Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where's that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Sloane Square. With the Countess of Connel. And of course - from there I - I was the scullery maid 
then, and then form there I went to - Seymour Place, in the kitchen - well there wasn't so many servants there, but - you see - you had to keep moving on to get money and more experience. Well then from there, I went to - Hatfield House, the Marchioness o
f
 Salisbury. And also - she had a house - in Arlington Street, by the Ritz Hotel. And - we used to go weekends - before - the footman and I, and - the - cook - to - Hatfield House, because we had - used to shooting, and weekend parties. And then we came ba
c
k on the - that was on a Friday we went, we came back on Monday. And then we used to stay - in the tower house, for about two or three weeks. And then we'd - perhaps move on, in the summer, to - Salisbury, to Cranborne House. And - there we'd stay - for t
w
o or three months. And while we were there we went to Stonehenge, and stayed there all the night, trying to see the Druids come, but no Druids, or there was no blood on the stones, which was supposed to be. You see, the sun - was supposed to - set on thes
e
 stones and you saw the blood. But we never saw any, and we stayed there all night. There was all the servants - the footmen and housekeeper, butler, stewards and all the lot of us - used to go - to see this. But then we'd come back and then we'd go to Ha
tfield House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was Hatfield House near Salisbury?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Hatfield House, no, that was in - Hertfordshire. Yes. You see, we used to go by train or by their own - bus. Then they had a chauffeur - that - for the staff, and a bus you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was your position in this place, were you a cook by then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no, I was - only a kitchen maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a hierarchy in these places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was four in the kitchen you see. And then from there - from Hatfield House I went to - Hammerton Pla
ce. And - that was at the Marquis of Salisbury. And - we used to travel - to the Moat then at Maidstone. And we used to have six months in Maidstone, on the Ashstead Road that was, and six months, in Hammerton place. And there, I used to meet - the presen
t
 Queen, and princess Margaret - as little girls, because their - them living in - what - what do you call that place now - oh - by the Ritz there was a - I forget the name of that street, anyway, it - it used to back onto the - Hammerton Place, and we use
d
 to meet them, I used to see them playing - in the garden there. And also used to - walk along - and see Princess - Royal, that was Princess Mary, when she lived - with Lord - Harewood. In fact I lived two doors away from there, in North Hawley Street, I 
worked. You see we didn't - we didn't stop in our jobs - as I tell you, you had to move on to get more experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did the employers think of that, did they not want to lose you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, they - I suppose they knew all this sort of thing. 'Cos 
the chefs didn't stay long. See, you were under - chefs and you - yes, 'cos you was getting more experience you see, and more money, you had to do it. And you cold get the staff them days. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who got you the job first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well Jacksons, Piccadilly, and that's the name of the street - that they lived. The Royal Family. 145 Pi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 cadilly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you get the job initially, did you apply for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we was recommended. You see Jackson was the grocery shop. And therefore - you just go
 into the - office and say - where you were working, and - had they any vacancies. We didn't have to go to no - employment - exchanges.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What were you doing between the domestic science school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's what I went into, the kitchen. And that's what I kept up. Kitchen all the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you went straight from domestic science school to your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I took up cooking. Yes. Yes, and - that's how - I started at twelve pound a year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was living in all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. And at
 - Lady Salisbury, we used to have beer money, two and six - a month, two and six laundry, and seventeen and six - our wages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would you live, what part of the house would you live in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Top of the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did all the servants live in the top then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - yes. Yes, mostly. Oh yes, 'cos there was a good staff. You see, there was four in the kitchen. There's four in the kitchen, and there was - seven housemaids, and four footmen, then there was the steward and the butler. Housekeeper. 
Oh yes, it was a very big house in Arlington Street. And of course you see, in Hatfield House of course it was bigger still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever see much of the -?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The other people were doing? No, we never got outside the kitchen. Kitchen was our place and - there we stayed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it very strict, the work conditions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, we was quite happy. Mind you we worked a good many hours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time did you have to start in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we - six o'clock in the morning, and perhaps would
n't be finished 'til about - ten or twelve at night. All depends what - there was on you see. If a - her, ladyship went out - and his Lordship - to dinner, well then we would be slack. We wouldn't have no dinners to do, 'cos we didn't have no teas or noth
ing. The stillroom did that, the stillroom too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Separate from the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. So we had no coffee to make, no toast, no scones, no cakes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would they have for breakfast?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, well - they would have from th
e kitchen - would be - bacon and eggs, and cold ham, you know, all done up with a - frill and the - bread crumbs all sprinkled over. And then there'd be fish. Such as haddock, or fried - plaice, whichever they preferred or sausages, but - otherwise we - w
e used to then have to carry on with the next meal. Get the lunch ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would they have for lunch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well for lunch they used to have - three courses. Or four courses. All depends show many visitors there was. If there was a lo
t of visitors, which we used to have on the weekends, well they - they would have - they'd start with - cold meat. Entree first, entree, not cold meat, they'd - such as scrambled egg - on toast. Or cheese on toast or sardines on toast. And then the next c
ourse would be - veal. And then - vegetables. And then the next course would be - cold pheasant or partridge. And then a - then they would have the - sweet, such as - a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 souffl\'e9}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 , perhaps a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 souffl\'e9}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  of - strawberries or - lemon souffl\'e9
, and then there was the cheese and biscuits, which came out the stillroom and - also the coffee. But once we sent the sweet up we could have our own lunch. We were finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would you have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In the kitchen. We never went outside the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would all the other people have theirs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they had the servants hall. You see, the - housemaids - and the footmen and the scullery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 man and all that - and - he'd - the scullery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 man would be with us but the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  nursery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 boy, he would be with the - housemaids
 in the servants hall. And then the - steward and the butler and the cook, or chef - whatever it was, they would go into the - another room of their own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they'd be all together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 All together. There'd be like three separate places you see. See we never mixed with the others, we were - was always -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There'd only be the three of you in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Three or four, you see. Three or four, whatever there was. Sometimes there was four in the kitchen you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What exactly would you have to do then as a scullery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - well when you go as a scullery maid, you - you go to - wash up the plates and all that sort of thing, but they had a scullery}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 man as well, because he used to do all the copper pans. And the - you know, and - and
 lift all the hefty - heavy pots, he'd do the saucepans. But the scullery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
maid herself, she was in charge of doing the - skinning the rabbits, plucking the pheasants, and birds. And then the second kitchen maid, she would be in charge of doing the - vegeta
bles. Because they didn't only have - just plain cabbage. You had to get all these fancy vegetables, to go with all the separate dishes. See, sometimes you had to have - make a - basket - of - tomatoes. Well you made that - cut the tomatoes, scoop it out,
 
and then you'd put peas in it, to put round the dish. And then you'd have potatoes, very thinly chopped, and - and then ring 'em and make 'em like bunches. You see, you had a - make your dishes - all different, and your veg all different, although it was 
only just - plain potatoe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 or - or - tomato or - carrots, but you had to make them all fancy shapes. But we had a proper - things to make them with.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you have any time off during the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, not very often - not very much time, just enough to g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 
o and wash yourself and refreshm}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 en}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 yourself to come on again - we'd have a cup of tea, you see, in the - 'cos we didn't get no teas as I tell you. All that was done by the stillroom. So therefore - that time we'd be about from say four - if w
e got finished at four, from the - lunch work, and then we'd - have a cup of tea and - well, a bit of bread and butter, then we start for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would they eat for dinner, the same kind of things again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 More or less, yes, it
 was the same sort of thing, but made to look different. They'd have soup you see. And then they'd have this here - entr\'e9
e and - and then - meat, fish - fish come before the meat, forgot that, they'd have a fish course, then they would have the meat course
. See they used to have about seven courses. And then they'd have - pheasant, and that was done with a salad and chips. Crisps. I never saw bags of crisps them days, and yet I've been making - thousands of them. Used to make them. Yes. And you - and put '
em away, you know, and then - they was always ready - when we wanted them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You wouldn't ever come into contact with the people upstairs during the working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ay then would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not very often, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about people like the butler and the stewards and the footmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Only when they came into the kitchen - to give orders. If they came to see the chef, to give an order. That's the only time you met them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did the butler rule the whole servant household then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not the butler, the 
- who was the other man I said - steward, he was the boss of the lot, the steward. The butler, he was only a - over his own footmen. And then there was a valet, used to dress his Lordship. And her lady's maids used to look after her - Ladyship. And then w
e
 had the - governess.. Two governesses, one up and - one under, and she used to talk French and all that sort of thing but - we didn't come into much contact with them. And then for the youngest children there was a nursery. So you see, there was always t
h
eir trays - to do. Well - the - second kitchen maid had that to do. Put her food on her plates and - see to that, then there was the - secretaries, there's two or three secretaries to see to, the - hall boy used to come and bring the tray in, and we used 
to send her her dinner up or lunch on that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So there'd be about twenty servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh - forty. Forty. 'Cos there was a - there was always outside, there was about - twenty bothy, what they called the bothy, they used to look after the fruit - and t
he - summerhouses. And then there was their own - there was their own - policeman, their own postman, and then there was the farm, their own dairy. There was two in the dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was this all in the town itself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well it's like a little town, this is at Hatfield House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where is Hatfield House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Hatfield House is in Hertfordshire, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about in the town dwelling?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that - that - everything used to come up in hampers. All the food and that when they was in town, all that wa
s all sent up in hampers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many months of the year would you spend in town and how many in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we'd have about three or four in town. And as I say we used to go the weekends - to Hatfield House you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you were trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ling around quite a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh quite, used to have the handsom, you know. We -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you call them the Lord and Ladyship or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, well yes M'Lord and no M'Lady. But - I was there about - two years. Then I moved on to - to the Lord and Lady
 - to the Lord Mayor - the Mansion House. I moved on to - to the Lord and Lady - to the Lord Mayor - the Mansion House.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that a big place as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh very big. And of course we had a - chefs there. And they used to have quite a lot of banque
ts there. And I was the veg maid - only. And I used to have to do - twenty - dishes - of spinach, twenty dishes of peas, twenty dishes of potatoes, 'cos there used to be about - hundred - in the Egyptian Hall, they used to have these big receptions, dinne
rs. And - and then there was the chef - two or three chefs, 'cos they used to have other chefs from - other places you see, and the same we used to - have butlers, there used to be about fifty butlers. Well they used to be from these other ladies houses.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Fifty butlers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. And they used to be from these other lady's houses, and they used to come there as - night out see, and a bit of extra money you see. But of course it was a very grand time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said all the servants lived in the attic area, would you have sort of separate rooms or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well there'd be - well the - the kitchen was on their own you know. There'd be about three of us in a room. Of course the - chef, he'd have his own room or the cook. But she was always chef trained yo
u see. Just a - just the same as a chef, only that he was a man and she was a woman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh I got on very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You enjoyed working there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I did. If you done your work you - you never got told off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you didn't really come into contact with the Lord and Ladyship that often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did they treat you when you did get in contact with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh, they used - they treated us well because when we had these big dinners 
- they used to - Lady Salisbury used to send down - two and six each - to the kitchen people, so that we could go to - the theatre or a show.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How often did you have time off during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we had an evening a week. One evening a week, say 
- four - to ten. We had to be in by ten. But Sundays very often - we was - at Hatfield House. They used to go away you see, so therefore - we had to go with them you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you first started work did you give the money to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I 
did. And she used to give me - perhaps a shilling back. 'Cos I - or two shillings back but - I got a pound a month. And that was big money that was. Yes, I got a pound a month you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had all your accommodation, food, clothing and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. And she used to buy my clothes you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did her Ladyship ever give any moral guidance to the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh what - yes, we used to have to go to - church every morning,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Every morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, used to go to church. And - hav
e a little service. And - used to put a little bit of lace - across our heads, and go in our little clean apron. Of course we always wore print, we never had anything else, only print. And a white apron. But - come Christmas time, she used to give us a li
ttle dinner. In the staffs hall, and then that's when we all met. 'Cos the hall was a very big place. So that's where we all met you see and - we had a - gram}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 phone with records. And we used to have a - oh, get together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was this on Christmas day or before Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just before Christmas. But Christmas Day we never - never stopped, nor Christmas Eve, working very hard, Christmas Eve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose they'd have everybody round on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. House used to be full. And all their relatives and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen if you didn't get back by ten o'clock on your night off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we got told off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would tell you off?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The chef or the - or the cook, whoever it was you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever feel homesick when you first started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh - oh did I, yes I did. I remember one - when - I went - first started - in Pond Street - Sloane Square, that - the cook there she was Scotch, and she was a real nigger driver. I only stayed there three months, and - I used to
 go home crying and say - oh no, mum, I can't go back. And she says, well, you must go back. So one day she say - she says, I'll come up and see the cook. So of course I didn't mind going back that night, 'cos I know me mother was coming up to see her. So
 - when she came she had a little chat with the cook and she says, you know, you - you can lead her but don't drive her. I always remember those words. You can lead her, but don't drive her. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did the lady of the house supervise all the housework personally or did she pass orders down through other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, she had her own Houdoir where the - you take your book, I've go}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 
t a book here with all the menu}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s, used to take up to her, and she would - say well we'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ll have this and we'll have that, and cross out the book what she wanted. That's how we used to - know what she wanted. And also - how many would be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever feel lonely in these places or did you have lots of companionship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - we used to have a laugh amongst ourse
lves, now like - Hatfield House they had what they call a - a copper hole, you know, the scullery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
man, he used to have to - do all the big - soup - pans and all that sort of thing, well they were - nearly as tall as meself, the big ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was heavy work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. Had to keep all the saucepans, the copper saucepans, 'cos everything was cooked in copper. And he used to sing to me. Come down my copper hole. And I used to sing, I don't want to come down your copper hole. And then we'd laugh a
nd he'd say, come down my copper hole. Come down my copper hole. And I used to say, I can't come down, your copper hole. Well - you say that made the day go you see. Otherwise if you wasn't - as I tell you, I've always been - a happy person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What were the others like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh some were miserable. But we didn't have time for them. Never had time, was too busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was the washing sent out in these places?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. But - at - our own personal washing was sent out - but - her Ladyship and his Lord
ship and all the family, that was done in the laundry on the estate. They had a laundry maids for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Does this apply to all the places you worked at?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, only that one. H}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 tfield House.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about places like the Mansion House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh the Mansion House, that all went out to the laundry. And - so did Beavor Castle. Duke of Rutland's. We - that was in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's in Leicestershire isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Grantham. Yes, I was there and that's where I got married from. I went as first kitc
hen maid. And - then I went to - the - the chef left, and they asked me if I'd take over the cooking. But unfortunate it was a lot, because there was all these shoots - besides - doing for the - the gentry, and all these nurseries. In fact it was really t
oo much at twenty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I had four girls under me. But - Y
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You met your husband there you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And I met me husband there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was he doing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was what they called a groom of chambers. His work was to
 - he had a little office - just inside the - servants hall, and - there they used to - he used to see all the - to the phoning, the post, for Her Grace and his Lordship, and all the visitors, and - and also - if His Grace or Ladyship wanted anything in G
r
antham he used to - see that they got them. He'd either phone up or tell the - chauffeur. And then he - he used to see all the shoot come in, like the grouse and all the pheasants, they all had to be counted. And then they were put away in cold storage. S
o it was quite a busy -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have much time to see each other though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, very little. Very little time. We might have a - two or three hours a week - all, that's all.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would it coincide with his time off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he'd - yes, in the
 evening, if they were away for the weekend, then we could just get out and - walk round the grounds and - used to sit in the boffey, what they called a boffey, a little - house in the grounds. But - otherwise we never got out together you know like - goi
ng to Grantham or anything like that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you were doing these jobs did you ever see much of your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they ever come to see you to see how you were getting on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, it was all done by writing. No, no, well in fact my mother couldn't come - cost her too much, and all the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What were all the other sisters and brothers doing by this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - listen, they were - they were - in the - at home working, you see, the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were the only one who went into service were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
And the other sister. The elder sister, she went into service. But the - of course then she was - just a - not so big, she only got eight pound a year, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you say you used to get three pound a month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A pound a month. Five shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In these houses who would make or mend the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh the housemaid. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who was responsible for repairs and improvements to the house, would that be from outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, they had their own men - on the estate. They had their own cottages. Used to bring them in you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you say they had a nanny?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there many children in these houses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well the - the - Hatfield House there was Lord Ce
cil. Forgot - forgot if there was any girls. Don't think there was any girls, don't remember any girls. There's two brothers, and this Lord Cecil's that's just died, he's the same age as me. - So - I was with his - mother and father. Yes. -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about the Lord Mayor, did he have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
I didn't see much of those. They were only in for a twelve month you see, well I just see - one Lord Mayor in, and did the year with him, and then I saw him out and in a few months - with the other one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of hours would the nanny do, do you know anything about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What with them, no, I didn't know much about what they did upstairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would Lord and Lady Salisbury spend much time with their son?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, they used to have them go i
n and see them and that. Oh yes, Lord David his name was. Oh yes. And then there was Lord Cramborne, his elder - brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would do things like dress and give him baths and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh well, he - he'd have the valet, for the - yes, the valet would see to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would he see his parents, what room in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes he had his own room and they had their room. But I suppose they - well after that - you know, he must have gone in and - see em perhaps for tea. 'Cos they were very busy people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did they do, were they sort of in Parliament or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose they were to do with diplomacy and the Foreign Office and that sort of thing were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 All that sort of thing, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember if Lord Cecil had any taks he had to do in the home himself, or was that all done for him by servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Servants. Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he do anything himself to help his parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, not as I know of, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would the adults eat their meals, did they have one big room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they had their own dining room. Their - and then the drawing room they used to have tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would the son eat with them there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - he - he'd be - he'd be with his own - tutor, he used to have a tutor. Had his own man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 serva}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
ts you see. He used to go around with him you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of cooking equipment did the kitchens have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh it was all copper and - big - big stockpots. Great big stockpots as big as me. And that's where they used to get all the soup}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787  from see. Well I couldn't lift}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 'em. And then they and - in the house at Hatfield House - there was the bread - used to make their own bread. They used to bake that in the war. Like the bakers - and they used to bake the bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they ever make any bottled fruit and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh plenty, well - see - the housekeeper used to do all that. That wasn't done in the kitchen. All the bottling and that sort of thing - was done by the housekeeper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they make wine and beer and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they do all that there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose they had a huge vegetable and fruit garden did they at Hatfield House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, well there was about twenty or forty gardeners, besides all this as I told you, the boffey - that only looked after the - the g}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 u}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ard - the - hothouses, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many people did they have to look after the gardens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I should say about twenty to forty gardeners. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they keep livestock and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, oh yes, their own dairy. And their own - sheep. Pigs. Oh yes, and chickens. Plenty of chickens.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd have meat quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Oh in the kitchen they used to bring in the - the lamb, all - just chopped down the - the middle, the whole side of l
amb you got it and then you used to cut off your leg or - whatever you wanted yourself. 'Cos - you had your own meat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was the average number that age a meal at the place, either in the country or in the town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well perhaps - you mean the gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well there might be only - just her Ladyship and his Lordship. You see. But when he - they had - it was weekends more or less, was when we had all these big parties. And they used to come down for the shooting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no tinned meat. We had to do all that ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time did Lord Cecil go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh that I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who put him to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 His - his valet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many rooms would there be to sleep in for the gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I should say about twenty. About twenty. See I never saw much of the - house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have a bathroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How often did Lord Cecil have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I couldn't tell you. See I - I never come in contact with that. You see, none of that, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have the same food as the Cecil's?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, if - what was over we used to be - put on the kitchen rack, that used to keep hot for us you see. But the servants - they used to have vegetables, all 
fresh cooked, cauliflower, greens or potatoes or peas every day for lunch, and - roast meat. Or perhaps cold meat. But there was always veg and salad and a sweet. And the same at supper. Used to have - cold meat and salad, then cold sweet. Like fruit and 
junket. Or fruit and - jelly or - anything like that or - jam tart. With custard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Do you remember any birthdays that Lord Cecil had, did you have any special occasions when he had birthdays or anything, would there be any special cooking for instance on those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no. No. If they did that would all come in - cooked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen on Christmas Day, what kind of stuff would you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - Christmas Day we were - very busy. 'Course the cook used to make the cake for Christmas. And 
there'd be about two or three tier cake. 'Cos it'd take her about over a week to do the icing. And the cake was made here three or four months before hand so that it could - mature.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was the main course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 For Christmas? Well they would have - the usual, you know, this - the soup and then the entr\'e9
e and the fish. And they'd have the turkey. And Christmas pudding and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
ince pies, 'cos instead of - instead of them having - a lunch, they would have a cold lunch. So that the staff - could have their Christmas dinner. And then - at night, they would have their Christmas dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you all eat together on Christmas Day in the staff or would you still keep the same three separate quarters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We used to keep our own selves in the kitchen and 
they used to - but all the other staff all used to - get together, like the steward and the lady - maids and all those used to go into the servants hall, and - all - have their meal together, the Christmas dinner together, used to call it Christmas dinner
.
 And at breakfast time we used to go up to - the - big - reception - hall and meet her Grace or her Ladyship, Lady Salisbury and - she used to present us with a piece of - print material for our - Christmas present, and shake hands with us. And thank us f
or what we'd done for her. Very kind lady. And very nice too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you come into contact with Lord Salisbury very much
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, very little. Unless you saw them - going along in the grounds.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose you wouldn't know much about what they did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. No, nothing. No. Same with the Duke of Rutland's, was just the same. Same sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember what the Salisbury's thought about playing on Sundays or anything, were they very strict on that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they take much interest in politics do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I don't know. See I didn't come much - contact with their private lives.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You don't know whether he was sort of very interested in sport or racing or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, I couldn't tell you. I should think he was more political, myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he actually in Parliament, wa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5790247\charrsid6044787 s he a Lord in the House of Lor}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So would he be away from home very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That I couldn't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose he had lots of friends calling round?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I expect so. I should think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Had you ever met anyone like the Salisbury's before you took the job there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you'd worked for somebody for about three months, the first job you ever did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh, In 
Bond Street, countess of - Kinmull. Oh she - we didn't see much of her but as I tell you - she - she was a busy woman. And - had plenty to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of woman was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I should say what I did see of her wasn't much - only when I had an interview, but - she was a lady. That's all I could say.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did all these people give you references when you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, it wasn't them that give the references, it was done by the - their secretaries. Or - done by the chef. Perhaps the chef used 
to recommend you you see. The - her Ladyship wouldn't know you'd gone. They never knew, it was all done through the chefs - in the kitchen. You just say you're gi}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ing your month's notice and you work your month and you go. And you go to - Jackson and - tell them. What you want.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Before you went to domestic school did you ever do any part time jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I was - I had too many kids to mind of me own - brothers and sisters. No, I was well - occup - occupied at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did the younger ones ever hel
p the older ones in any way, the children when they were young, did the younger ones do things like errands for you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we might run - errands for ladies and all - for the neighbours. They might give you a ha'penny or - farthing
. Sometimes there was - couldn't afford it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have neighbours children coming into the house to play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, my mother never had that. She was - always kept herself. No, she always kept to herself my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was she an easy person to get on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes. But as you know she - just kept to herself and - then there was no trouble. That's how we go along now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 If you had a problem or were worried about something could you take it to her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could I take - oh yes, yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How about your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh me father was very strict man. Very strict. I remember one day - I was home on a holiday, and - me sister - me elder sister, she - thought she would - she - went out and she was a bit late coming in, 'cos we
 had to be in you know by nine o'clock, them days. And she - it had gone nine, so me father, he went - he popped up to Greenwich, to - the church, Greenwich church, which is St Alfredge}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \rquote 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s church, that historical church there, and he'd walk along and he'd s
ee her, perhaps talking to a young man with her friend, so he'd dash off back home, in come me sister, knock at the door, and me father said, where you been? She says, out with Minnie Rose. He says - has Minnie Rose got a bowler hat and a walking stick? A
nd I always remember that. Get up them stairs.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your father ever punish you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh - he'd tell us off. Oh yes. Oh Sunday morning was the morning for - for - us all meeting at the table, me father got us all together and - all our grieva
nces we used to have to tell him, you know, if me brother upset me or like - throw a face flannel at me and - I wouldn't - I resented it, or - you know, one or the other was upset, and he used to - have it all out at the table. Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would he sort of ever hit you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we used to get good hidings or - sent up to bed with no dinner, or tea very often - if we did wrong.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things did you have to do wrong to warrant that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh you'd really have to upset him. And as for m
e mother, oh - we - we - he - he used to not eat too much meat, but he was a great fish man, he liked fish, so we always used to have to go to the fish shop and get - skate or a piece of cod. Well one day I came home with it, and me mother smelt it, and s
h
e said, that's not fresh. Take it back. And I cried and didn't want to take it back. So she - made me take it back, she pushed it, you know, in me hands so rough, and I had to take it back and - and the man says, you're mother - what does she want for her
 money? And giving me the money back. So therefore I had to go to another fish shop, and get something for him. He's very particular about his food. And then another occasion, I went to get some corned beef, which is only eight}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence a pound then - they use
d to have big tins of corned beef them days. And it was lovely corned beef, but this was very crumbly, you know, soft I suppose. The pieces, he thought, oh - she's of a large family - but anyway when I took it home and my mother says, look at that, take i
t back and tell him it's for your father. They changed it. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember your mother having less so the rest of you could have more at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, we was all shared out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you allowed to have second helpings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, i
f it was there. 'Cos she always made - big rice puddings. See you could get - skimmed milk them days for a penny a pint. So she used to make rice puddings. And the rice was only three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hapence a pound. The loaves of bread was only tuppence ha'penny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did she ever bake her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, she never had time. So we used to buy the bread you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember whether your father used to have more than anybody else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, oh father was - his food had to come first. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen if he was on day shift, you told me about how you used to go down with his dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh day time, well then of course - he'd have his dinner, then we'd have - you know, vegetables. We had chiefly vegetables, we didn't have much - ni - meat. Vegetables and gravy. That was what we chiefly had.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would he do during the night if he was working during the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he used to take that with him you see. All - she used to pack him up you see - with his food and - in a basin. 'Cos he
'd been sleeping through the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you allowed to talk during meals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well within reason. Within reason. We'd get told off - if we start arguing. Be sent away from the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How was the meal served up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh on a plate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you do it from the table or the stove or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 From the stove to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have your own places, you say you used to have relays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - no. Yes, it all depends who was in and who was out you see. Some would be out you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You wouldn't all be at the table at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, not all at the same time, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How would you keep the food hot?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well she had this big hob. And a great big sauce - iron saucepan, with the two handles you know, the old fashioned kind. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could you bring toys or books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, none of that. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could you leave the table when you felt like it or did you have to ask permission?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - all depends how me mother felt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose it was her that looked after meals more than your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Oh yes, yes. He might help on the Sunday, if he wasn't working. He cooked the dinner then. Yes, he cooked dinner then, he'd take over that. While mother got us all dressed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would he do anything else around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh if there was any - repairs want doing he would.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he ever do the washing up for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And the washing. And washing he's done, and wash us boys, used to wash the boys. Could tell 'em off for - not doing 
their ears. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he make the fires and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he used to take us to Woolwich. Go to Woolwich Arsenal, you know, to see the - changing, the soldiers. Take u
s over the ferry. Oh yes, he used to love that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would that be on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Sunday morning. Take us on the tram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would he look after you when your mother was out, say at the mother's institute or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 If he was home, he'd - or let us in, you know. But she very often used to - be there, if she was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, mother used to do that, and she - we used to knit. And, you know, say father was coming at eleven o'clock at night, well we 
used to sit up, well - the elder ones always sat up with her you see. And then she used to tell us stories and - teach us to knit - our own socks. Stockings, but - you know, for the older ones and - socks for the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your mother or father make or mend the family clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He'd mend the boots and mother used to do the clothes. Oh he was always mending boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose with a lot of children they keep changing foot size don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Well one go down to the other if it wasn't worn out beforehand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you ever get new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we had new clothes, new clothes. No, we never had no second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hand - not like today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your mother have made them all or bought them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh she made them. And what she didn
't make she used to buy. Like - she'd make the boys trousers and all that sort of thing, but - the coats and caps and all that - she used to buy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where would you buy the clothes, what kind of shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - the - what they call the in and out shop
. We used to go - High Street, Deptford. And do most of our shopping. And there was always a - in and out shop there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would the older children help the younger children with things that they found difficult to do like getting dressed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Oh yes, they had to else they would - be told off, reprimanded. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So everybody mucked in and did their best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We did, we all helped one another. Yes, we - I must say we were very good family considering. Very good.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did your parents expect you to behave towards your other brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, we - if we - start arguing or you know, got nasty, they would - smack you for it. Not like today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen if another child hit you or hurt you, would they say hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They'd say, hit him back. Don't come to me with your troubles. You hit them, they hit you, you hit them back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How do you think your parents expected you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we had to respect them. Oh yes. If we didn'
t say - mum or dad, they'd soon say - what have you forgotten? Especially me father was very strict on that. Say mother. Or ask your mum. And say thank you, say please. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you think they brought you up to consider certain things important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, they bringed us up to respect people, and if we - had anything - given us - must always rite and - and thank them. And thank God - my children are doing the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well I think they was proud of us considering - there was such a lot of us. I think they was very proud of us. We never let them down. I think that's the chief thing. 'Course during the war they - worked in the - the war factories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Your father came off the boats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, he kept - no, he - he had to keep the coal going, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose that was crucial really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, very. Oh yes, he had to keep up the - coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would they think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - oh we weren't allowed to do that. And they never swore - in front of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen when grown ups were talking, were you allowed to join in?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, not - if it - you know - if it wasn't our conversation. Oh no, seen and not heard, that was the - that was w
hat we was. Sent into the other room or - go and play in the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your mother ever punish you or was it just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh mother used to have to punish us. 'Cos - sometimes poor thing she - you know used to get worried stiff what to do next.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 With thirteen children around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was a lot wasn't it. And her - and her being - like she was. Pregnant so often. 'Cos we didn't realize that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Quite a worrying time pregnancy wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It must have been for her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Do you think you received the ideas you had about how to behave from both your parents or do you think you got more from your mother or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I - I was only telling my daughter yesterday - that - me mother - was - I was very fond of me mo
ther, and as for me father, he - he - he did single me out a bit you know. If there was anybody to take out - it was always Lucy. He liked taking me out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And he used to take you to the Woolwich Arsenal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes. Used to - and - you know, if he went for a walk - I'd be the one mother'd have to get ready to take.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go on holidays with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Never. Never had holidays. But they went - had holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They did. They went to - Jersey once. And went to Ramsgate. But my grandmother used to look after us, and grandfather.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They'd come and live at the house would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. They'd - come every morning. Me grandmother used to come in the morning, and me grandfather used to come - in the evening.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long would they go away for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just for a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your father have Bank Holidays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he have paid holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, he got a paid holiday. Oh yes, he got the week - holiday - pay.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he get things like Christmas Day off and Good Friday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not if - the tide. It all depends on the tide see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So he wouldn't sometimes be there for Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no. No. No, 'cos they had to keep the coal up didn't they. For the gas you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you think other families the father would be home on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, if there fathers was working in factories - and that sort of thing, it's being that - he was on the water we accepted it, we was brought up to it. Going in all hours and -
 coming home all hours. And when we came in and saw him we just accepted it. He'd have his - meal and go to bed. Was always tired out. You see, and perhaps - he might be getting ready while we're going to school, or he might - be in bed. So we didn't - we
 had to be careful - not to make a noise up the stairs. Wasn't no - wasn't no shouting, nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you had meals were you allowed to eat what you wanted or did you have to have what was given you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We had what was given us. And what one didn't eat the other one did. That's how it was worked out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen if some was left uneaten?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - very seldom because - there was always somebody to finish it up, the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What if there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you just reach out for it or would you have to ask for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we could reach out for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way and sit up during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, as we got older we was taught that. Of course when was younger we had a spoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could you leave the table whenever you felt like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What order were you served in as a family, was it from the oldest down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - no, no, was - as you came in - so you were served.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you didn't have a sort of rota?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, no, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there anybody in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Unfortunate, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever play games with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we used to play bingo. You know - tippit - tip - tippits is it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Tombola?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Where you - tiddly-winks. Tiddly-winks - we used to play. And - shove hapenny. You know, put hapenny on the table and - just as a game, no money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was your father interest in any sport of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I never known him to go - play anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He didn't go to the races or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes - if he was off he might take mum to the - Derby. But that wasn't very often. And he might have a little bet but very little. Very shrewd man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I should think he'd have to be to cater for thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, 'cos he used to say to us - save up your money, be as cunning as a fox, and then you'll always have tobacco in your old tobacco box. He always told us that and that's how he - he was able 
- to keep us as he did. 'Cos we never wanted. And we was never without shoes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there other children in the area who didn't have shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh there was, but - he - he was - as I tell you, he was such a - proud man - that we had to be - keep our
 shoes cleaned and - keep ourselves clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he come from a large family himself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Yes he did. And his parents - they worked on the - at Greenwich Pier, on the boats, pleasure boats. They were - captain and skippers of the Golden Eagle and
 the Royal Sovereign - from Greenwich Pier. And they used to go - to - Southend - Margate and Ramsgate, day trips and then back again. And used to go for five shillings, a day. Yes. So all his people more or less - have been - water people, with the sea.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, we used to I get libraries but of course - I don't say we was always able to go and read it. Because - used to be - is that all you've got to do? There was always plenty of - washing up or - scrubbing. Or - mending, perhaps. Or a bit of knitting.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there any newspapers around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You was never allowed to read 'em. Me father had them. But we - we - we always had something else to do. Is that all you've got to do?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have comics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, we had a comic. But we used to hide those and - take 'em up in the bedroom. Read them in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember your father or mother reading much themselves, apart from newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The only time I - I remember me mother r
eading - was when - she used to read to us - stories, about the girl up in the attic. Her names was Mary and where she was caught up there and couldn't - couldn't find her way down and - there we were saying, and what happened mum, what happened - to Mary
? Wait 'til I get there she'd say. And then - eventually she found her way - down, and then the door - knocker would go and that was me father. Eleven o'clock at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you wouldn't go to bed 'ti about eleven o'clock?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was the older ones used to sit with her you see. We'd be about twelve or thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time would you have to go to bed before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh dead seven o'clock - into bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh put ourselves to bed. Up them stairs, go on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How old were you when you first put yourself to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - four. Three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you used to bath in the kitchen or scullery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, oh yes, the tin bath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How often would you have clean clothes to put on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Every week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 After bath night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Bath time. See that would be about Saturday or Sunday - morning, and then - me mother used to do - washing on Monday. We used to have get the wood and - chop the wood, and light the fire, copper. Then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember anything like a funeral in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, me father's funeral.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Before that, before 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh you mean a - I remember like the - King Edward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was thinking something more to do with your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No, no, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Like your grandparents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, they lived a good age.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you ever taken out}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 visiting neighbours or anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, none of that. Too many of us. Oh, too many.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you ever go out visiting your relatives or friends, your parents friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not very often you see because - there's such a lot of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about shopping, were you ever taken out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, we used to have to do the shopping. Unless mother was getting us a pair of boots, or a coat. Then - then we'd go out, to t
ry it on but not otherwise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go out of the Greenwich, Deptford area in those days or did you always stay in the same area all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we used to - go Deptford shopping with mother. Used to think a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of shops did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
All the shops, you know, there was a - oh we used to like - some chips sometimes, fried fish and chips, or - I used to as a - like - a cockle, you know. Me mother might buy a plate of cockles between us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you used to go out on the riverboats now and again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we used to go on the boat on the river.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you ever go as far as - you said you went to Ramsgate once on the boat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would that be a Saturday or a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Sundays. Sundays. That used to be the trip.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd get out and about quite a bit really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How would you spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh well, we were shopping, and I'd - and - and myself, I - I would be in the park with the chi
ldren. I used to have about four or five children - me brothers and sisters, not other peoples. And - we used to be up there all day. Me mother used to send - dinner up. A great big - pie dish, with a meat pie, and all the potatoes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would bring that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Me brother would, and - and she'd give us a spoon each, and we used to eat out the dish. About five or six of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A real picnic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say on Sundays you used to go out on these river trips and to Woolwich Arsenal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh then we - we used to take - sandwiches.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have different clothes on for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes, always a - dress, hat. And all clean underneath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents think it was wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. We always had to go to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of things would you do at Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well Sunday school we used to - sing choruses and - they used to talk to us. And - give us a text. And then if we - had to bring it next time and then - when 
we got so many we got a prize. A hymn book or something. Oh yes, we always had to go to Sunday school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you go on to church from Sunday school or just the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just the Sunday school. And the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And what about your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, as I tell you, me - father didn't go but me mother used to go - mothers meeting. On a Monday. The women}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s Own they used to call it, mothers meeting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would she go to church on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. No. She never got to church. 'Cos she was a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hristian woman you know in her way. Saw that we went.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it a church Sunday school or a chapel one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This was a - chapel one. Called the Bank - the Ragged school. In Bridge Street. And we used to go there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 don}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  the Sunday morning was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The - Sunday afternoon. And we'd go Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd go twice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes, twice. And then - like the older ones went Sunday evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen if you went down to Ramsgate for the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh well, we didn't
 go then, we - used to have to tell 'em - where we'd been. They didn't say nothing. There where was a Band Of Hope used to go in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was that about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was all about - Christianity. Band of Hope. You know, telling you to do good to 
people and - used to show you slides - of - like they show Vietnam war and all this - for the poor - Africans, so they used to show slides of 'em them days. And the missionary work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother go along to those as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. That was in the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever know anything about a temperance club, was there a temperance club in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was a temperance but - that was more }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hristian wasn't it, just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You don't know anything about what they did or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. Just talk about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hristianity.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say your mother went along to the Mothers Institute, were there any other things you used to do through the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, there was nothing else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have grace when you had meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that was up to us. You know, sometimes we'd say - oh mum, shall we say grace? But it wasn't forced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about family prayers, did you have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you taught to say your prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well we - mother left that to us. She never had time. Too busy getting undressed the others - the younger ones, getting them all to bed. 'Cos there was bottles to make and - bread and milk to give them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember whether your father or mother had any political attitudes or took any interest in politics during that period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh he was a great Labour man. Used to go and vote, and all that sort of thing and - I remember going to the Town Hall, and we used
 to stand outside - oh be great big - gathering of all the people, and watching to come out on the tape - who got in and who hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it very strong Labour round that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was a Labour - always has been. Although myself I - I was more for 
Conservative. Because I used to say well if it wasn't for the Conservatives I would have never had a job. 'Cos them employed servants - give us - there's nothing else for us girls to do them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever take any interest in politics yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he ever a member of the Labour party, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he ever take part in any activities like canvassing or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He just went along to vote?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just went along to vote with me mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
You say that sometimes men risked losing their job if they voted differently from their employers, did your father ever have anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about your mother, did she ever involve herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When your parents weren't doing their work what did they do, how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - father'd be gardening you see and - mum be looking after - the chickens or washing up - washing out blankets, you know, extra - laundry work - that wanted doing round the house you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did she ever take any laundry in for other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, Oh we had enough of our own. Oh we had plenty of our own without doing other peoples.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother ever have any other interests outside the home except for the Mothers Institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Never - heard of her you see. Not like today, all these clubs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did she ever go out to enjoy herself with a lady friend or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You couldn't really say when your father got home in the evenings, it could be any time, night or day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well you see mum was always busy with us. She was always - knitting or as I tell you darning or - ironing or washing. 'Cos he was a very strict man, so particular that - you - you couldn't neglect it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So - she was really working round the clock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
You - yes, you knew when he - he was home. Oh we used to get scarce - make ourselves scarce then - when he was about. Because he was so strict.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He wouldn't like much noise I suppose?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, and - you had to behave yourself, as he called it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he a member of any savings club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we had sick club. The doctor's sick club, used to pay - think it was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
pence a week, and - that included all of us - if we were sick, you know, got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 tonsillitis}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 or - bad cold or anything like that, we used to go and see him, and he give us medicine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How much a week was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
pence a week. And then - they used to put away - a slate club for Christmas. Sixpence a week, on the card. Used to go and pay that sixpence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would happen to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well then come the end of the year, we - the - we could draw that out you see. Which they did do and that used to get - extra clothes for us and - and all the - things 
we wanted. Buy the cakes and the Christmas tree and all that. Although come to that we used to join a - sweet club in the sweet shop, and pay ha'penny or a - farthing a week, you know, a day, whatever we could afford.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, not - very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They didn't give you a regular amount?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And if they did give you anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, well if we earnt a penny perhaps if we went - we ran a errand for a lady, a neighbour she might give u
s a ha'penny or a penny, my mother would take it and - give us a farthing for it. 'Cos got a lot of sweet them days for a farthing. Had four ounces a penny, the sweets.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you'd spend it on sweets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever save any money yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well used to try you know, buy - your mother and your father a present for their birthday. You might get four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence saved up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you had a birthday did you have friends in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 None of that, no. No. Nor me mother. No, no parties.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you ever go round to other neighbour's homes or to play or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No - because - was too many of us. We were well occupied on our own. As I tell you we didn't mix with neighbours much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you get on with your own brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Very well. Very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there any one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. Oh yes, you - you - you always single out one brother, it's funny. We always single out our own brothers - that we like, and - he's still alive, he's living at Greenwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How much younger than you is he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I should say he's about sixty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So he's quite a lot younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he goes down the list quite - oh yes. Bobby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you played mainly with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, you see, that's how we were brought up to play together that - we didn't look for any - body else to play with, we - we were all right ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we'd get told off if we was too dirty. 'Cos that meant more washing for mum.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents ever discourage you from playing with other children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, no. Oh when we went to school we used to - have friends call for us and all that sort of thing. Oh yes, but I mean - but
 as to have - children in your house and - you go to them you - you couldn't. Couldn't do it. They knew you see, we was - so many of us.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have anything like a hobby of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Knitting. I used to do a lot of knitting - and sewing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have any pets in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Rabbits and - yes, rabbits and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you eat the rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh, no, we used to eat the rabbits. We all - they were - we had those for eating. And same with chickens. If we got to many cockerels we used to have to - kill them off. Because them being noisy. And we had pigeons. I think we had all sorts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you do with the chickens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Hamsters, the girls had. Fetch in the house. The girls had hamsters. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever collect anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Seashells.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did you get them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The - when we went to - the sea. Perhaps now and again we'd get a trip to Southend. Wasn't very often but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How far is Southend away from Greenwich? About an hour on the boat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go fishing at all in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 T}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hames?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you go for very many walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, we used to go to the park you see. We was all in - always in the park or - on Blackheath round the pond. Used to go round and watch 'em - playing in the pond with their boats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there any bicycles in the family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No, we made our own toys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of toys did you make?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I used to get me mothers pegs and - dress them up as dolls. Yes. That used to be our - our toys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever play shop and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, we used to play shops. We used to get - perhaps old bottles - or anything like that we could and - buy these small sweets you know, and - pretend we was buying you know. Wrap 'em up in a little bit of newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about the boys, what kind of games did they play, did they play amongst themselves and the girls play amongst themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they - they had tops they used to play with. They used to go out and have whipping tops. And they kick a ball around, you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could they play in the garden if they wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, provided didn't kick or - the shed, the wire, catch the ball on the wire. You see. Wasn't - it was a nice long garden but - as me father used to grow flowe
rs in the garden, dahlias and - all that sort of thing, that - give very little room for us to play in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you separated between the sexes, sort of the girls played together and the boys played together or did you all mix together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We all mixed together, we all played together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say your parents saw quite a bit of their relatives, both sets of relatives did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes - well not me mother's, 'cos she died - they must have died very young, 'cos I don't remember - her mother nor h
er father. But me - me father's mother and father and - sisters and brothers and - my aunts and uncles, we were always visiting them. Well we - we were made to do it, go and see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were they very nice people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he - but we'd get told off if we didn't go and see them. Why didn't you come and see us, and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents have any friends outside of relatives?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they ever go out to see people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. Never had time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your mother ever bring anybody back from the Mothers Institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Or your father bring people back from work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say they sometimes went down the pub in the evening did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. No, none - that's what I mean thank God, I had
 no - no pub crawling or nothing. That's what I tell you he was a very strict man. He - he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did much of that go on round there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Oh plenty of it went on, you always saw - drunks and - fighting and all that but - I - my - I was alway
s proud that my parents - now as I've grown up and think of it, that I had no fighting or - no abusing or nothing like that. They had their tiffs but was never in front of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents ever do anything amongst themselves you know, outside of y
ou children. Did they ever do anything together, such as play games sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
No, no, no, no, they never had no evenings out like - only as I told you - me father'd take me mother out - if he wasn't working on the weekend like to New Cross Empire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
People often divide society into different social classes or groups. In the time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one group and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh there's always been the second class and the - poor class. Oh yes, you always have got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who are the second class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well I should say they're these people that - been able to make a little bit more money and - like the shopkeepers and all that sort of thing and - the - they were - bit higher than you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about the clergy and teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh they were very good. They were very kind to us. No, we were of a large family, they always had a kind word for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What class would you put them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh the - they - they came round and - and they came and t
alked to you and - see how you were getting on, and all that sort of thing. And encourage you to go to Sunday school and that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they come into the house for cups of tea and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, none of that, no. No. Oh my daught
er does, the one that - no, but then you see, they didn't do that so much them days, but - my daughter does now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who do you think would be the most important people in Greenwich, the Greenwich area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kinds of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Those that used to live on Blackheath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where - well they were the people with the - houses, and keep a maid.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would they be in the second class or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I suppose you'd call them the gentry at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So there was the gentry, the second class and the poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You see, we never had - never knew the Lords and Ladies, not then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Because they lived in a different area of London?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Should have to come to - London for that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Amongst the poor class was there any sort of grades of poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They were all one and the same to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, you might meet the Jones's trying to - keep up with the Jones's as they say. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it possible for people who were poor to move out of being poor? To go into the second class or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, nev - never heard of that. No, I never heard much about class distinction, not them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you think when you went to work in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh well - I did - I did think I was then lifted up. Oh yes. Oh yes, I - I was a lady then, and I never looked back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did your parents and your brothers and sisters used to think when you used to go home occasionally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - me - brothers, bless 'em 
- as - used to stand down the bottom of the road - when I went to knock at the door on me half day off - and - waited 'til I came in me mother'd open the door and let me in. And then - they'd come in and they'd say - who's that lady mum? Yes. You'd hear '
e
m whispering. And I'd be sitting in the kitchen. Go on, that's your sister. What - what's wrong with you? Oh I thought it was a lady. Oh bless 'em. Yes. I used to make them trousers out of - the old sacks, you know, the flour sacks, we used to have the - 
well bags they were, fourteen and twenty-one pound bags of flour, and I used to wash 'em and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
ake the children trousers and - whatever I could. Lining -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you were working or before that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When I was working. And buy a bit of material, check material and - make 'em a pair of trousers - for the boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have holidays when you were working in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we got a fortnight a - a year. Two weeks a year. Well then I used to go round to my sister, who lived down in - near Hungerford.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Berkshire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I used to spend my fortnight there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was this the one who was in service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She - she'd been in service but she - she got married young you see. When she was twenty. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was it a paid holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes, with pay. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have bank holidays when you were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh none of that, no, no. Never knew what they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You never remember of any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh nothing like that, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever do any apprenticeship, you did this domestic science training course didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well me brother, he - he - he - he went as apprentice for coppersmith. Yes, he went as a coppersmith, and did his time. And then he went to America. Yes. Came of very - couldn't have been about - saw much of him then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of people would you say went to church and what kind of people went to chapel, was there difference between them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - there was no distinction only just that I suppose - it was - sort of a thing the
y - was brought up to do or - made to do and that was that. And for the love of it some of 'em would - I used to be happy singing all the hymns and that, and hear the stories, used to like. And then we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The old bible stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. And when I got home me parents used to say, well - what did - story did you get today, and we used to tell 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of people would the clergy and the teachers associate with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Ve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 y}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 nice, like ourselves. Just like ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They didn't think themselves above anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no. No, they were just real - you know - homely - people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Was there anybody you were brought up to think of as a real lady or a real gentleman? Did you ever hear anybody called a real lady before you went into service?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh well - yes, Lady Bad - Baden - Powell. She was a great - one for - in the Scouts movement, in fact she was - godmother to one of my brothers, Lady Baden - Powell. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a Scout movement in London at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And at Greenwich. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go along to it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, me sister belonged to the Guides. Me brothers was in the Scouts. And we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You never joined?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I never had chance. I always had the kiddies. And my father used to say, now
 come on - if he asked us to do a job - like - such as cleaning the knives and all that, and he used to say, on my guard of honour, I clean the knives tomorrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you always have your set jobs to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he - he did. Some had to clean the 
- the boys had to clean the knives, the - the silver and all that. And we had to do the ironing, the girls, and the mending. Oh yes, he kept us well busy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you were still at school were you ever told to sort of touch your cap or curtsey to people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no, none of that. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there anyone around who was called sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. Not at Greenwich. Very working class - place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there any people who were very poor in Greenwich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh plenty of poor people, plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you think of anybody as being poorer than you for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were saying about some people at school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, some'd come without boots and - shoes, but then - you see we always looked on them that - t
he parents couldn't manage. Just their way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there any families who were considered rough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, very. But then you see - if the mothers used to go drinking in the pubs and the fathers and that well that's what we used to get in the back streets. We used to get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there ever any trouble in the streets? With drunkenness on a Saturday night and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Round the corner there was, in Roman Street, 'cos they - there was the pubs you see. And they'd be there drinking all day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They didn't have the short hours then did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social group at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well she was always brought up to be res - respect - people and that and I suppose that's
 why we did. What I can see of me aunts and uncles - when I did meet them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember whether there was any distinction between craftsmen and labourers in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I - I didn't - take that notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about the policemen, were there many policemen around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, plenty of police. Used to pickup the drunks. And of course them days he had - they didn't have police cars like they've got today to take them in. They used to have them on a - wheels - like a long frame, bed thi
ng on - on two huge wheels, and used to strap them - yes, used to strap them in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they'd be visible for everybody to see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh you could see them, but they were - wheeled off. And there was work houses for people that didn't work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were saying about the work houses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, because you see - if - if you didn't work and - this - and they saw you - laying about - 'cos you - you used to get some of these - mentholated }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  meth}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 late people that drink methylated - methylate is it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Meths drinkers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes - they used to - take them in, because - they was a nuisance - to other people you see. But - otherwise - you didn't see much of it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever sort of hear stories about the work house or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. O
H yes. And we was always threatened - if you don't behave yourself I'll put you in the work house. Or if you don't - go to work - you know, when he was - the boys started working, they would turn round and say, well if you don't - do your job properly, yo
u know what you've got. There's always the work house facing you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So the people didn't like the idea of the work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, the - it was always threatened with the work house. Much as to say, well if you don't want to work, you can always go 
there, and they did make you work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Your family had nothing whatsoever to do with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, thank God, we had none of that, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have anything to do with the Parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, no. No. No, we was always - able to keep our
 head above water as they say. As I tell you, dad - was a very shrewed man. And he was never out of work. Which was a great thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a lot of unemployment around before the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh there was always unemployment. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a Labour Exchange and that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, they were Labour Exchanges them days, used to go - twice a week. But the - you didn't draw money like you do today. They draw - they'd - find you a job. And - they'd give you two or three and you had to take o
ne. There was no going back and saying, I can't do that. You had to try it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What if there was - no job available, was there always a job there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was always a job. Yes. Oh yes, you - there was no need to be without - work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were people afraid of the police then at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, they were. Oh yes. Because you see one look at the policeman - because the way he walked, it was always a - more or less - elderly man, you don't see - young boys like you do today. They were always more or less - fatherly. And so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you ever told, if you're naughty I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, very often. Very often. The police'll be after you. If you don't behave yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have any trouble with the police?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No police - no trouble. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How do you think the police treated the people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh I think they were a bit hard on 'em, they used to push 'em around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In what way push them around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, the - if they caught them, you know, doing anything - t
hey - they'd - they didn't let you put - for instance - I saw one man, he - he must have been stealing or something. Well - they went round to his house. And - they took - got him out of bed, and he just managed to get his socks on and trousers, and that'
s how they took him to the police station. Walked there. Oh they were very hard on 'em. So I don't suppose - that's why we had so many cases as there is today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Because people watched what they were doing more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh they did. They knew what they wer
e in for. And there wasn't none of this so much as paying fines. You had to do your time. And you had to do the birching the boys. They got birching them days. Oh yes. Oh yes, they got - what they call - the back - the strap - across their backs, so many 
strokes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you remember any sort of children at the school who came from the work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. Never met any. No, no. Never met any families like there is today, you know, put into children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s homes and all that sort of thing. We did - we neve
r heard much of that them days. There may have been but I never - came up to it. Never experienced it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you see much of the landlord at these houses you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Only once a week. He just took the rent and off he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would he do any improvements or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, you used to do your own. So my father or my mother - used to do all the painting and the papering - themselves and repairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say he was quite a nice chap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You never had any sort of bad time from him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh no, no, none of that, no, the - well the rent was always there and - and he always asked how the children were. And that was that. He went off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Does that apply for all the houses you lived in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose so - o
f course I suppose he'd be nasty if some of - some of 'em didn't pay their rent. But as I tell you, we never had much to do with the neighbours.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you wouldn't really know what was going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, we didn't, we didn't know what was going around u
s. Well you see you couldn't very well, for one thing you'd always get one neighbour would say - could I have a cup of sugar or - tea and all that, well my mother could never do it. She could never afford to let them - have it and not pay her back. Which 
that's what th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 ey were doing. So she never sta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
ted it. And told us girls never to do it. If we - when we got married. 'Cos we could have done the same thing, I could have done it many a time meself. And have done me. People coming and - and borrowing half a c
rowns a week, and - and they've had just as much money as I've had coming in. But I used to let her have it - and then - in the end I had to say, that's all right, don't pay it back. 'Cos I knew she wouldn't come again. That was the only way to stop it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have any people wandering round who were sort of trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 l}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 lers or gypsies and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. Yes, plenty of gypsies. Oh yes, 'cos - once they told me - I was going to - not marry the first boy but I'd marry the second, which I did do. And I'd have to go to a big place - to meet him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they forecast that all right for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they - those were very true the gypsies them days. And they used to sing - lavender, you know, sell their lavender.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have little encampments around Greenwich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, on Blackheath. On Blackheath they did. They used to have them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did the locals think about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Nothing. Never heard anything. But of course I couldn't tell you - what the people on Blackheath thou
ght about them. But we never heard nothing - not at Greenwich itself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There's usually a lot of stigma against gypsies isn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - there is today. And yet to think - years they've lived haven't they. I would like to see a settlement for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They've got one now haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I think the Government has really - give them a place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But they're still not applying it properly apparently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well you see - you see - they don't live like we do. But today I think the gypsies are - given more civilised.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Was there anybody in the district that people strongly disapproved of do you remember, or any way that they showed that they disapproved of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no, we - we had none of this - distinction like - with the you
th - like there is today. There was none of that on then. There was too much like - Band of Hope's and youth clubs, and all that sort of thing that - you never saw the boys. Out in the streets. They always had somewhere to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You can't remember anyone being forced to leave the village area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
No, no, no. No, none of that. No. Come - Christmas time it - or - say New Year, see the old year out and the new year in, we'd all get the glasses and go to the front door, and we'd have a dustbin lid and - w
hen the bells were ringing so we banged at the dustbins and that and - wish everybody a happy new year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever go carol singing at Christmas?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, oh yes, we used to go carol singing. And - coming back to the new year you know, we never l
et no - blonde - come into the house. Always had to be a dark haired person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well because we - they used to say that was bad luck, I don't know why. And when the new moon's on we always - and even today if we've got any on us, will
 turn it over - for new moon and when we see the new moon, we change it you know. Turn our money. But it mustn't be through glass. So if I see the new moon now and it's through glass I won't do it. No. These funny little things, yes, you just carry on. We
ll you get these old dears - from the clubs doing it. When we talk things over you know, about what they've done and what in their days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Everyone's doing the same things still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I think there were a lot more traditions in those days weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
It - it was. It was. You had to keep up, you know - such as Christmas was Christmas and - Easter was Easter and - you had your hot cross bun for Easter and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would give you the hot cross buns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well our mothers, we used to get 'em for a ha'penny each, or four of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 
\endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  three}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence. You know, we used to get them cheaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there any special Sunday schools on Good Fridays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes, they used to open up then them days, and we used to go there to get out b
un. Might get an orange as well, but - hot cross bun was what we went for. It was - called the Shaftesbury - City - Mission. And they still keep that on now. The Shaftesbury Mission.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that in Deptford?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This is up in London, the Mission it - th
e mission itself but I mean - the centre but we used to - all belong to that you know, these Sunday schools. There's even one round here, In }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 P}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 arbury - Barbery Road. Shaftesbury Mission. Round under those lights.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have anything like the Easter eggs and things.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - yes, we used to get a - Easter egg each you know, ha'penny each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Chocolate bunnies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Ha'penny each, Easter egg. Ha'penny ice}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 cream.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you ever given lessons by one of your parents or a tutor or a governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, there was never no time for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The first school you went to would be at Blackheath you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, Dutton Street would be my first school. I was very young you see. I was only about - three. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you have to go to school on your own then or would your mother take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, there was plenty of brothers and sisters to take me. 'Cos we're all going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But weren't you the second oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh, me being the second eldest well that would be - me mother used to take us then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You'd then take the older ones when they got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When they got - you know, old enough, but - me mother, she'd take us to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you first started what time of day did you have to go to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I think it was always about half past eight. When I were about - three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you come home for dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We'd come home - come home for dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 dinners at school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, none of that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well I used to be glad to get there. Yes, as a change. I used to fall asleep, I don't mind telling you. I used to be asleep - asleep half the time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did the teachers think of you being asleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they used to - be sorry you know, they knew but - they had to tell me off of course, 'cos of the other children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there many children who fell asleep during lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I don't know, I know I did. But - I expect there was. And then - we used to go home and then the next day 
was same thing you know. Sometimes you'd - didn't get to school, 'cos your mother want - had to go out and take the other one - to - to get the - see the doctor or something. We had doctors coming in at the school, to - look at you and all that sort of th
ing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How often would they come around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I think they used to come about once in six months or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have dentists and things as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, we had none of that. No, none of that. But then used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did the teachers mind if you didn't get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes, she'd tell you off because you were losing your lessons you see, but then you see, having a large family, there was always someone that caught some - like measles, or got whooping cough, or mumps, an
d therefore - you had to stay at home to help mother you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You'd have to send a note in or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who would take the note?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Always a - oh - oh yes you daren't go back without a note. Used to send you back home for one. There was no -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you send a note before you stayed away or did you just bring one when you came back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You - you take one when you go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were the teachers very fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, some of 'em had their favourites. Some had their favourites.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What would they do with the ones that weren't the favourites?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well they used to be always shouting at 'em and - putting 'em up in the corner and put your arm - hands behind your back, or make - or make you write out - fifty or a hundred times, I must not talk, or I mustn't do this, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have the cane and things like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, there was a cane. Several children got the cane. For being naughty at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you have detention?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Oh yes, they got - many a time they got that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did the teachers think about things like manners and punctuality and speaking properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well being old fashioned you may depend - that was well rubbed in. They made you pronounce everything you know. A
nd I think them days are better than today. Like - er - they - they - amen, we used to say Amen. 'Cos that's the word as it's - spelt, but now it's amen, and - and they write these days - as they think it's - spelt. Whereas we had to spell it - them days,
 
say if it - you had took - I took it, well you put I took it, not I took it or whatever it is - that the children talk today. That is the teaching of today isn't it. Oh yes. And I think it was better. And that's where you get your - yes, thank you, no tha
nk you. But - oh - today's language - I don't understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they expect you to be tidy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh very. And clean, and clean hands. You were sent home. You wasn't sent to wash 'em in the lobby. You were sent home to - wash your hands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Wouldn't children like that so they could get out of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - it was a disgrace you see. You were taken in front of the class. Oh yes. And they'd make an example of you. And if you said you - had a sore throat, they brought you out and looked to see you'd got a sore throat. They didn't accept your word.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So in other words you wouldn't make it up because you wouldn't like to be kept out in front of the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. You had to - and then they'd send you home. And tell your mother to keep you warm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would the girls be treated any differently from the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Well boys were in the boys class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There were different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes, there was no - no mixed chil - like there is today. There was the boys school and the girls school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your parents show much interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes, they wanted to see you get on, although we - weren't able to do much homework.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I should think by the time you got home you had lots of things to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well we did you see, there was always - the children to do for. And help mother with the - work, you see. 'Cos she'd had enough all day - cooking and - one thing and another, washing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you help here with the evening meal when you got home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that was all done you see, she did the cooking. But we'd have to do the rest you see. And laying up the table and - washing up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would your parents ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they had an open day, when they could come and - you know, and lo
ok at our work. I'm afraid I didn't have much work to show them. 'Cos I was away a lot. Yes. Yes, I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Helping with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's right, or - mother had to take one to the doctors, so therefore I had to stop home and - look after the baby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And yet you say you got your scholarship at the end of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, I managed to get that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that purely in domestic science?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well it was writing and that sort of thing you know. And I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What subjects did you have at school, apart from reading and writing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Composition and - arithmetic. And - handicraft. And we also - used to take - we used to do plays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of plays did you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we used to do Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs. And Seeping Beauty. All 
that sort of thing and - Shakespeare. Oh yes, there were plenty going on. Oh yes, I think we had good schooling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did the other children like school as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, some of - well they used to cry, didn't want to leave their mother but - they - som
e'd be gone home and by time she got home, they'd be in the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  house, and yet she thought she\rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
d left 'em at school. So she had to run 'em back again. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there much truancy in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, not a lot. They were too strict on you. You see - i
f you - weren't there they used to send and find out where were you and why - why were you not at school you see. There was none of this - letting it go on for a weeks, and then suddenly discover - the boys - not been going to school which is thing all wr
ong. And today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There's a lot of it round Deptford at the moment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - and there is here. The Hammersmith School, that - what school is that they've got there for boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 YES. Oh we girls got secondary, even the - a
nd that was wartime - here. One went to St Marks. And the other one went to Portobello. And then what they didn't - learn at school, they went and - taught theirselves - at night school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever got any night school or just this domestic science course?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's all, just done domestic science.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long was that for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I just did the eighteen months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that paid for by the Labour Government?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could count a year's scholarship. And I - out of that I used to buy - my uniform. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had to have a uniform?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes, I - oh I was a very proud girl. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have a uniform at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, there was no uniforms - only when you - if you won the grammar school. But otherwise there was no - none of this uniform business.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you left this school at fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, and went into the - domest - Duchess of - Aberthway - the Athou Institute, Deptford. And - there we did three months cooking, three months - laundry, and three months - dressmaking, and book - book keeping.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And from that you applied for your first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, and from there - and off I went with me tin box - to Pont Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did your mother think of you going into service, did she approve?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well there was 
nothing else for me you see. That's all there was. Of course; she missed me. But the other girls as I tell you, they all went in war work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did they do after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They - you see, and after the war they got married. 'Cos they was get - coming on - to the age of getting married you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Otherwise if it hadn't have been for the war they'd have been in service like you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes - no, they didn't want to go to service. No, they didn't want to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you always want to go into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I - I think that was the only thing I could do at that time but - I'm glad I did. 'Cos I really enjoyed it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you think working in service changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. I was happy and - I was brought up to respect people and - you know. And I had a better understanding.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you think there was any division of interest between you and your employers for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, we here brought up to respect them you see, that we didn't notice no difference. 
I just - accepted it. So - that's how we got on. And as I tell you, I - I met me husband, 1926 - and - we got married from the - Duke - and Duchess of - Beavor or Bouroir you can call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was in the actual castle was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, Beavor Castle, a
nd - I was very grateful how her Duchess - came to the back door, I can always remember it, on her horse, to say goodbye to me, and thank me. You see, 'cos it was such a great strain taking the first - position and having the four girls and all that - wor
ry, like - what with the parties, and then having all these shooting - parties weekend and responsible for everything that - I sort of - you know, had a - nervous breakdown, that I had to give up. Yes. And by getting married that sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Eased it off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It did. It - it was some other interest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So how long had you known your husband when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 About six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you actually first meet, did you meet in the corridor or in the kitchen or where?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He came down to give some instructions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh he - he - he - no, he used - he came down to - he was looking after the secretary at that time, and he - 'cos the boy was on his holiday, and he came down for her meals. So - I suppose I must have laugh
ed and talked about you know, had fun with him and - then we went out - to - Grantham, we managed to get a day out. And we came back in the evening and - then when we got two or three hours we went into the - grounds in the boffey. Used to sit and chat. W
ell then - he left - that was the starting of it, he left and then I - didn't want to be left without him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long was there between?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where they'd lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that the first time you'd been there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. I just had one week in Belfast. 
And we stayed at Bangor. So - in a way I'm very interested in this here - trouble, but - I'm glad me husband's - not alive to see it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he Protestant or Catholic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A Protestant. You see - most - people there were Scots. That's why I can't get o
ver why - they have this distinction. Because they were - if - where we were staying, in the boarding house in Bangor, it was all - married couples you know, having their honeymoons and they come from Scotland. To spend it in Belfast. And I was always und
er the impression - that they went there to work because of the shipyards that was there, and that's where they was getting their living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I think a lot of the Protestants did originally come from Scotland.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They did. They did. But regard to the - 
this Orange business and all that, no. You was never - none of that. They never told us nothing about it. We never knew anything about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It's suddenly come into the limelight again hasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your husband go to chapel or was it Presbyterian church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was Baptist. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, he didn't go but he always let the children go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they go to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 aptist church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, they did. And then they ended up - well one is still Baptist, but the other one belongs to All Souls, Langham Place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that a Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
That's Church of England. That's where they got married. And the children were christened there. But the other daughter's children were christened at - Culver Tabernacle, Ba
yswater. Yes, she brought the boy - from Reading, the son, and had him christened - baptised as - in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  All}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Souls - not - I'm getting mixed up - at Culver Tabernacle, Bayswater.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you go to church when you were in service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Always went to church. And me husband, he used to get the alter - ready. For the - Duke for Rutland - minister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They had their own minister did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, they had their own minister and their own chapel in the house, so we had to go there you see, and - take th
e service, and he used to prepare all the lessons for him and - do all that, on Sundays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why did he leave the Rutlands, you say you couldn't do without him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - it wasn't his job. He wasn't happy at it, he wasn't - wasn't his work. He hadn't been used to it. You see, you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You talked about it before he left, you know whether to get married or what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, although we were courting. No, he just out of the blue - when he came to see me - at home. 'Cos he had a move - he had - yes, 'co
s he had a room the back of Barkers here at Kensington. He'd always lived there. So - he just said, shall we get married? And I says, yes, all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What were you doing down in Greenwich, weren't you at Beavor Castle at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I just - I just went to the - like to get the fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was your holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, we just took that fortnight and got married, and then we went straight on to - Agatha Christie's place, and we were there just - four months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But did you sort of decide just as soon as you started your holiday to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't know anything about it until then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no, nothing. Used to correspond - you know, write to one another.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you say it was just a fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. I had one letter. I've still got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Between you leaving Beavor Castle and you being married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, I've got one letter. Just saying how he - he missed me and I missed him and that but - otherwise - I never had anything, or heard anything 'til he - came and saw me at home, came to Greenwich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And this all happened inside a fortnight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How could you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Special licence. Yes. Yes, we had to pay the two pound.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't think to get married in church or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well we didn't have time you see, 'cs we'd already got the job. We fixed up the job - yes, we fixed up the job - and I says - I wouldn't go in unless I was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he meet your parents before you decided to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, nothing of that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did they think of the sudde}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid461496\charrsid6044787 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ness of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, they just, bless 'em, they - managed you know, put the - managed with the boys and that and let us have the front room, 'cos they knew it was only for a few days. And then off we went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did all your family go to the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, just me mother and father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So there were just the four of you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You weren't engaged or anything before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, we got that after. We got the wedding ring. We bought that at - Lewisham, he bought that like between us. See?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say you got engaged after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we got that at Victoria Street, in - one of the Jewel shops there, along Victoria Road. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever have anything like love spoons or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I suppose you wouldn't have time to save for a bottom drawer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh nothing. Although I'd got things for me bottom drawer, you know, like - we'd given one another presents - like the - our workma}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
es. We used to buy sheets and pillow cases or give - silver spoons and all that sort of thing for the bottom drawer, and blankets I had well I used to buy in sales. So I'd always - lived in hope of marrying.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was this the first boy you ever brought home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh no, no, I'd brought home a footman before then. And it's funny, he lived at Bury St. Edmunds and he had - his people had a - public house. Yes, yes. I was supposed to have business, but I never got into
 business. The gypsies said business. But I never got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your husband never want to go into a pub after you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we never had the money. He'd have liked an off licence. But we never had no money. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you do after Agatha Christie?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, after her we went - we came to London. And - there we - we got a post at - Mr Enson, he wouldn't take his title, as Lord Farringdon, like his brother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh he was a - lovely old gentleman. He just wanted
 to be himself. So that's what we did. And - that was - he lived in Princes Street, or Princess Gardens, the back there of - what's this big place where they have all the - Albert Hall. Just off the Exhibition Road, that's where we were. And we was careta
k
ers. And we went down to a place called - Deacon - near Hungerford, and this - he had a big country house there, and we - used to keep it - the bedrooms aired and, you know, and tidied up, and he'd come down weekends and my husband used to wait on on him,
 and I used to do the cooking. And we had a housemaid with us, so we were all right you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long did that go on for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - I - sorry to say that I - felt for me first child. I became pregnant. So - when it got to - about seven months me hu
sband told Mr Ensen. He was very upset.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you leave then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, we left. And we went and bought a - went then into this - cottage, at Ham Common, and he was butler at this school. Yes, he - he - there was a school at Ham Common, and he even - the big jockey, what was his name -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Steve Donaghue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, that's right, his children used to go to it at that time. But he - he - wasn't cut out for that work. Very proud man, my husband. So - so what we had to do, I had the baby, they couldn't tu
rn me out the cottage, so I had my baby, and - we had to go to the Justice of Peace to give me sanction for a few extra days, as I wasn't fit to move - and then we got out of the cottage, because there was another butler waiting to come in, with his famil
y.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did you move to from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
From there - we - went to Surbiton. We managed to get our furniture in, although we'd furnished up this cottage, you know, as much as we wanted it, and we - hung a lot of the chairs and - things in the big cupboard we had in the room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you do at Surbiton?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
We just - looking around for a job and we couldn't get one - for a long long time, so we just lived on the - little bit of savings we had. And with the child as well. But - we got a job, and
 - we went up to Bath. To Colonel Brenton. Place near Chipping Sudbury. But when we got up there, and got our furniture - all moved up into a - warehouse there, the - place that - Colones Brenton had bought wasn't ready. So we couldn't - we come back agai
n. 'Cos he wanted my husband to do - odd jobs, and we couldn't do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you didn't actually work again after your first baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes, still doing it, you know, 'cos me mother took it. Me mother took the baby. And I used to pay her so much 
a month - for the milk and that. And we carried on up there you see, but as I tell you the job was no good so we - had to come back. And then - we came to Fernhead Road. And we had the baby with us there and - there he went into - Whitehall.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 As a Civil Servant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, as a Civil Servant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you work then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I didn't work no more then. No. No, 'cos we got the flat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So I suppose looking back to the time when you got married you wouldn't have any holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, never had holidays, he wouldn't have holidays. He wasn't a man for holidays. No, he never wanted a holiday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did it come as a surprise to you when he said do you want to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It did. Because I didn't think you know - being the - the way he's been brought up
 with the - having the - servant and all that sort of thing, I didn't think I'd be good enough, being of a large family. But - we got on very well. And we had our two daughters. And we never looked back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you look back to when you were working in service was there a sort of hierarchy amongst the servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
No, no, no, none of that, no. No. They just accepted us, well you see - I - I've always been a personality that, you know - can always pass things over thank God.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that when you were very young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Very young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You used to do what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Put 'em all on the - make 'em all sit on the bed, and I used to - get 'em - and pretend I was this and I was that, acting. Always done it. And dancing - as a fairy and all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever do much sort of acting at school you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - well - what my leading role was - when we had - Snow White and the Seven, Drafs, I was in the singing - for Snow White, but - otherwise I didn't do no acting. Well I was never there, I was - they couldn't rely on me you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever do any nativity plays or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
No. No. As I say they could - you see, I was - I loved all that sort of thing and I like ballet dancing now, if there's any on the television, that comes first. I love ballet dancing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you see that programme Upstairs, Downstairs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that very true to life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes I think it was. Yes, very true. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your husband ask your parents for permission to marry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Certainly. Oh yes. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you there at the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Well I went in the other room or - made meself scarce - at the time, and - and - he went and asked me father, or told him he wanted to get married, and me father said,
 yes, that's all right. And told him what he was going to do and - of course he said could he keep her. And after it was all over he told me - well - you're married now, you've made your bed and you lay on it. That's what they did them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They were quite happy about the whole thing were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, very. Of course we didn't have no reception or - we put on a little tea like a chicken and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your brothers and sisters come to that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh well they were there, yes. 
Of course they couldn't make it out, you know, me being married, and him stopping there, not going. They was wondering when he was going home
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It would be completely out of the blue for them wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, well - well you see, I'll tell you wh
at there, when I was twenty-one, my mother had her last baby. At twenty-one. And - of course I was shocked. I didn't want to - go home or anything, at the time. But after two weeks - I made me way home. And forgot all about it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was probably
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well of course I was twenty-one myself, see, and she goes and his this - baby. But then she -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said there was a sequence of about eighteen months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - well - I think she had a - few miscarriages and that you see, and change of life. You 
see, the - the boy then I suppose would have only been about - seven, when she started having these other - three more. So now we get - oh well, we're two families. I have to tell you -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So she had seventeen in all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, she had - take three away 
from thirteen - ten. Three later on, you see, and of course there was a lot of difference. To you being twenty-one, then going home and - seeing another baby there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The baby would only be about fifty now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, quite. Quite. Well, it's a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you ever see him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Not very often. He's living at Swanley, you know, in - just off - Erith, Bexley. They're all living that way. But I don't see them much. Only when there's funerals and - weddings. That's all. They write to me now and again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When did you tell your parents that you were getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh it was a shock to them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you write to them straight away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I was home on the two weeks holiday. And the second night I think I told them. I said, mum, he's asked 
me to marry him. But where are we going to put him? See I didn't ask if I could. I said where are we going to put him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Had you given in your notice to the Duchess of Rutland by then
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh we'd left, and he was staying in his room. You see, at - back of Barkers.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She didn't know when you left that you were going to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh nothing of that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did she know that you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - well - what - me mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The Duchess of Rutland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, no, no one knew. None of 'em knew. Or knew that - I was courting him I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You say that you got an engagement ring after the marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that because you don't think you can he engaged without a ring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's right. Well it is a natural thing isn't it? So when we was down at Victor}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 a and - we had the money, so he said, what about a ring? So we looked and see what we wanted and we went in and got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have any other rings between you before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no. No, he's a proper bachelor. Proper bachelor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you choose your wedding ring you say you went up to Lewisham and he paid for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - oh we was thrilled - 'cos they only cost five pound - them days, twenty-two carat. Yes. Five pound, twenty
-two carat, the best gold you can buy, but - he just tried it on me finger and - then he put it in his pocket and he said, there it is still.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You've still got it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have anything like eternity rings after the marriage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, none of that, no, no. Just had the engagement ring. He says, come on, one day and - out of the blue, when we -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long after you got married was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, long time. Yes. We was at Victoria and he says, what about a ring? And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you fix up the Agatha Christie thing, did he know about Agatha Christie when he left the Duke of Rutland's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, we did go to - to and employment agent. He was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that before you got married or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Before. We were - we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your husband find out and then tell you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Yes. And then we had a bit of an argument, because I says - I'm not going in with you - unless I'm married. So that's why - we had the - special licence. So I was only really married a week before we went - to Agatha Christie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What day was it you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 February the sixteenth, 1926.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that a Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh, I couldn't tell you. No, no, but I mean I - I just - I couldn't say whether it was Saturday or a - midweek day. I fancy i
t was a midweek. I know we had a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you have liked a large wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh certainly, I would have loved a white wedding. But - I wasn't really prepared to - him to get the job together you see. See he - he got this post - as - yes, and to go t
ogether, and I thought to myself, oh no, Lucy's going to get married and play the game properly. Which I did do. And we got on very well. But as I tell you the - the post - we'd been spoilt having so many servants, and having our own job, that when we fou
nd we had to be jack of all trades - we just couldn't do it. It was too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you do anything special the last week before the wedding, like having a hen party or a stage party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh nothing like that, we never had no time. There was all the time getting the room ready.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you wouldn't have any last day at work I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh nothing of that, no. No, we was all living on our wits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did your husband see you on the wedding day before the ceremony, were you both staying at your house the night before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, he came the next day and we all went together on the tram. On the tram car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you wear for the wedding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh I was in blue. They say blue and then you're true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have something old, something new, something borrowed, something blue?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I never had a chance for that. But I know I was in blue.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did he wear?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well he - he had just his - suit you know, was always a smart man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have any flowers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, none of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Or confetti or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. Just a plain wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there someone to give you away, do you do that in registry offices?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - the gentleman - at the registry office, he found two people there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just two people in the office?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, that's right. Came forward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you have any photographs taken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Then you say you went back to your place for a small reception?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, at night, we just - you know - a drink and - roast chicken we had, I know we had a roast chicken, and we had a cake.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Then you stayed at your house a few days and then went on to Agatha Christie's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 About a week and then we went to Agatha Christie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he carry you over the threshold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh none of that, he was too old. Being a bachelor he didn't understand those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember attending any other weddings when you were young which were different from your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Going back to your schooldays, do you remember whether there were any gangs or anything like that in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
No, there was no gangs. Only girls used to - you know, wait on me. I was always frightened when I was going home. And they used to - come from a lane, you know, in Bridge Street, and they'd - rush out '
cos they lived in the back street, and they'd say, here comes Smiler. I suppose I was always smiling you see, even them days. And - they'd chase me, and - that's all the difficulty I had in them sort of ways. Or saw -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they ever catch you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, 'cos I used to run, but I always stopped, you know, 'cos I knew what I was going to get, and then I'd just make quick run.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What kind of girls were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well there was back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 street girls you see. Poor - poor class you see, from another school. Yes. But they just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there girls from your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh they wasn't girls from my school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were they like that though at your school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I never noticed any, no, 'cos it was a church school I went to and - you know, they were
 very strict about that sort of thing. But these were from bad parents, at the back. I do know that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember anybody at school being left out of things and sort of on her own all the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not as I know of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you'd be about fifteen and a half when you finally left domestic college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, schooling and everything, I said goodbye - to my schooldays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you have any regrets as about your education at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, because - I'm - I'm proud to think - that I - was able to go into that and win the scholarship, and wear the uniform.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did any of the other girls do the same thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes. In fact the - girl that was in my - we used to have - class A, class B, and class C, you know, so that one class would b
e doing the cooking, that - term, and then the next class - would be doing the dressmaking, so that we'd - go round you see, in sets. There's about thirty of us. And this Connie - Castle - that was - in my set with me, let's call it set A, her son has mar
ried my n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ece. Now isn't that funny. And at the n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 eces wedding I met this - Connie Castle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And did you know about that, I suppose you must have known before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well no, I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't know who it was at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, not 'til I saw
 her there. And she says - oh, I know Lucy Beesley. She said, yes, that's my aunt. She says, she went to school with me. And of course we were, made - you know, quite friends but - I haven't seen 'em since. Although they - me n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ece and her son are missiona
ries now, out in - South America. In - the African - or is it the Indian field. Yes. He's doing the ministering part and she's doing the nursing. Isn't that funny? Yes, and yet - they were both - you know, well educated, and the n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ece and so was he, her son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you went to the domestic science college were you living in there or were you still staying at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was at home. Coming home each - I used to have the food - all day there, and just go at nine and went back about half past four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Did things change a bit, did you do different things now that you were away from church school, were you allowed to stay out longer at night for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you do anything different at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You - no, you could never. Only meet them when you - were at school, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't go out together in the evenings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, none of that, no. Oh wasn't allowed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you practically sort of continued the life you'd been leading before you went to domestic science college?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They call me Lucy. I've always been called that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you were a child I think you said about how your mother didn't encourage you to mix too much, she rather kept herself to herself?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, that's right. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Would you say as a child that you played with any of the neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, you played with the neighbours children, but I mean - as regards of - talking - as regards of talking and all that 
sort of thing you know like - standing at the door or over the garden - my mother never did any of that. She used to keep to herself. In fact she had plenty to do but apart from that she always did that. Kept to herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And your father was quite like that too was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Very thrifty man. As he always said, save up your money - be as cunning as a fox, and then you'll always have tobacco in your old tobacco box.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But he did have this sort of work group with the watermen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes
, he worked for the - the - gas company, Greenwich. What they called the Liversey. And he used to - he was the driver of the dumps that used to go and up and down the Thames with the coal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you just shoed me that photograph of the outing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh 
yes, and they used to of course - have their outings, in the summer. They all used to - go out for the day all the men and boys. And at Christmastime - the children had a party. Fr the children. Yes, we always had a party and they used to give us - when w
e came out - orange - apple, and a bag of sweets. After giving us - an entertainment in the evening. Every year we got that. We used to look forward to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The outing, you said that was from the Beehive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, that was a public house. That's where they all met. And the bus used to come up and then take them out for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that the watermen's pub really, the Beehive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - not really, because - it was a pub in - where I lived along - few doors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was in the street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, it was in the street, but they all used to meet there - and go off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there a lot of people working for Liversey's in the street then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, more or less gas people you know, 'cos it was only down the road, the gas company and - and I use
d to go and get bags of coke - for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence a bag. Yes, used to take the barrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 For your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes, you could always get a bag of coke for four}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 pence. Yes. It's very handy. And then I used to - take me father's dinner. And the b
arrow with me, and he used to come aboard - 'cos I used to - his boat - or his tug would be in the - moorings as they call it, and I used to stand on the bank and shout out, Liversey }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 b}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 oy. And me father would come up, wave his hand and then row across to th
e steps, and then he'd fill it up with wood, and I used to - wheel that home. Give me - give me father his dinner and then - wheel the - wood home and that used to do for our fire.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He got that from the river, the wood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was on night work sometimes was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh he - he was on all hours you see, he went with the tide. You see? He - as the tide was up then he would go to work. You see, he couldn't - say - well I'll go at nine to five, he'd have to probably go in the - morni
ng early, when the tide was up. That's how he - could work his tug.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And there were a lot of children in rather a small house weren't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - well - me? Here, a family. Oh yes, we were - about - seven of us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I think you said that one reason for your going into service was that .....
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
To make room for the other one - to - take my place you see. Because - it was getting a bit too much and another thing - that's all there was for me. You see, the war came on. So instead of me doing me schooldays - well the - scholarship that I won -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And your eldest sister went to service for the same reason?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, she went to service too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She lived in as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And so - that's what happened there, we had to - I was fortunat
e because - I was - at this here - domestic science that I'd won, and I - and the matron there as we called her, the head one, called her matron you see, and she got me my job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The first job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Up in Bond Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You mentioned Mrs Hunt's registry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In Duke Street. And I think it's still there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you describe that to me, what the place was like at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well you went in and there was - offices. And you just - called you over and asked you what you wanted, and yo
u told 'em that you wanted a - a - a kitchen job. And - was it - you done - told 'em that - if you wanted a scullery maid or - second kitchen maid or third kitchen maid, you see, and they would - fit you in. And - you paid 'em so much - for the job.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You paid them for the job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes. But what it was I couldn't tell you know, because it was 19 - 16 you see, it's a long time ago.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you had to give them the references?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh you had to have two - two references. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And those I think you said you got from the chef rather than from the mistress? Was that always so?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh that was when I got older.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But earlier on you had them from the mistress did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. You see, the - me first one was from the school - matron
. And then from on then well then - I'd get one from where I worked you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When was it that you got one from the chef?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was in 19 - 17, I used to go to - I worked for the Honourable Mrs Bailey in North Norley Street, and of course - that 
was quite near where - two doors away from lord Harewood, from Princess-Mary, and I used to walk along just like anybody else, and would never take no notice in Mayfair.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you got a reference from a chef there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And - he used to send us - to - Jackson's. Of Pic}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 adilly. Oh yes, that's where I used to go and get all my jobs. Or Fort - Fortnum and Mason.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So Mrs Hunt's you didn't use first of all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 We used her first, when I was only - fifteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And then later on you used Jackson's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Later on in years, then I used to go to the - Jackson and that because - they got to know me - by going and getting the coffee. See they had special coffee, and we used to get the grocery from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And they ran a registry as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - no, it was just done through the desk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So it was an official kind of one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh - no, no, no. No. Just a desk. You see, the chefs would go in and say - do you know of a - anybody like - myself, wanting a post? Kitchen job. And they would say, oh - well recommend me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And would the chef say what pay they were willing to offer you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, you got that and it wasn't very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said you moved around partly to get a bit of a rise?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that's the only way you got it y
ou see, 'cos you might think I was a wonderer but - the thing is you had to do that - because - as you moved on, so you got more money. Now when I was at - Lady Salisbury - what we got there was - we didn't have like a - wage, it was called board - board 
- board lodgings, and you got two and six, a month, for washing and two and six for beer money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What do you mean by two and six for washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was two and six a month.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They paid you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 For doing their washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, for my own washing, that was for a month. My - my aprons and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had to pay them or they had to pay you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They paid me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 For doing your own aprons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well sending it out. That's what we were allowed. Two and six a month. And two and six a month beer money. Everybody got beer money.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So those were sort of extras?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And you got seventeen bob - seventeen shillings - board and lodging as they called it. A month.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That board and lodging you were paid there, that was like a wage, that was for you to spend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, it was - yes, yes. Yes, that was like a wage, but of called it in them days - board and lodgings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But in practice what that meant was that you were paid one pound two and six each month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you could spend that how you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, that was my wages. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It's a funny arrangement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was you see, to all the other jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you went to get the job though you could know what you were going to be paid beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes - yes, yes. yes. Yes, 'cos you made that arrangement - when you were - interviewed the chef - or the cook. You never saw the lady. She never interviewed you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about earlier on though when you went through Mrs Hunt's you were interviewed by the lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, that was by the cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I thought you said that the Countess of Kinarl interviewed you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, well - yes, that was me first job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was the only time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. That's right, yes. Yes. Oh the Countess of Connaugh
t, yes. Yes. After that, well then you just saw the chef or the cook, whoever you - went, you never saw the ladies.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But every time you left it was because you wanted a better place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. To better myself. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't like the first job but apart from that you didn't really leave because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh I - no, no. No that - that was the only way of - of getting more money you see, moving on all the time. To better yourself, you see, and of course then you got a better chance - of growing u
p like - from the - scullery maid, to - first kitchen maid you see, otherwise you'd still be - there for years and be nothing, but - nobody did stay in their jobs long, them jobs. Everybody was always on the move.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In your first job in the house in Pond Street, could you tell me how many people there were in the household there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 - four housemaids. There was th}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ree in the kitchen. And there was - a - footman. A - butler. And a valet. And a chauffeur for the car. And there was also - a - yo
ung lad that used to take all the trays up - to the nursery and - and see to - the general you know, in - boots, cleaning the shoes and that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you were the scullery maid there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, I was under a cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you didn't like the cook?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well she was - you know, a little bit too fussy. She didn't give me time, and of course I was - very shy, at that time, and nervous. And I used to wash up, take the things to put away - on the dresser and drop them and never knew I'd dropped
 them. I didn't even know I'd dropped them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And she was unpleasant to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Very. Was always, go on, hurry up, and I used - when I went home, I told me mother I can't go back there no more, and she says, well come on I'll - I'll take you. And she
 took me back home - to the - Pond Street, and saw the cook, and told her. You can lead her but don't drive her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So she was a bit better after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You said that you were so small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh very small. But - they were going to Yorkshi
re - to the country place, and of course - that's how I got out of that job, that they couldn't take me, because - the pots were bigger than me. You see, they were huge stock pots. And the - I couldn't lift 'em or - it's where they used to make all the so
up, and put all the bits and pieces into it, and get the stock you see. So I left there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What sort of hours did you have to work in that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh from six to - eleven. Six in the morning, 'til eleven at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was quite common to have to work as long hours as that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you feel that the cook expected you to work longer than was really necessary?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, she couldn't work - work me no longer. I'd had enough. I'd had enough - I was ready for me bed. And it seemed
 no longer I got into bed I had to get up again. Oh it was terrible days, in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What time off did you have there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I used to have - one Sunday, every fortnight. And - half day a week. When I was in town. But of course when you got to t
he country, you never - got any - thing, your time - when you were spared.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was pretty standard in all your jobs was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you think about the jobs the hours and the time off didn't really differ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was the wages really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's it, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Could you do what you liked when you went out for the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, I used to go home. Tuppence all the way as they used to say them days. From Victoria to Greenwich. Get on the tram,
 or a bus. And go all the way to Greenwich. And I used to get off at Greenwich church. And then walk down the road to Greek Bridge, and that's where I lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But they didn't ask you what you had done, did the cook as you where you'd been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh she knew I'd been home you see, she knew that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had to say where you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh yes, she knew where I had gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In that first job where did you sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well we shared a room, you see. Up the top of the house, and - three of us in a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What sort of a room was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Just plain. But - it was a bed. And - dressing table and chest of drawers. All in one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you had a bit of furniture?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who were the other two that you shared the room with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The scullery maid. And the first kitchen maid.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were a scullery maid there weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - I was a scullery maid, so I shared it with the - second kitchen maid - and - that's all there was, only three of us, in there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There would be two kitchen maids and a scullery maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How was the work divided between scullery maid and kitchen maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well you see the scullery maid, she was the one - that did the washing up. And she also - had the birds to do, pheasant
s, rabbits to skin, and all the copper pots to clean. But I can tell you - by time that it come to teatime, you'd just finished. And then we started again - had our tea, which was in the kitchen, we never mixed with the - household - whatever.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You mean the other servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And - we used to then - have our tea, and it was time then to prepare for dinner. And then I started cooking - the veg then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 As scullery maid you cooked the veg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was the kitchen maid's job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well her - her job was - to - do the roasting and that you know and - the nursery cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So she was really cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - in a - plain cooking, yes. Plain cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So right from the first job you were taught a bit of cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you knew how to do it anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Oh yes. 'Cos when she was out you had to take over. Oh yes. When she went out - for her day's outing - you had it to do. Take the lot, the - washing up, everything.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 With this first job when you were unhappy did you feel that the cook took any sort of interest in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes, bless her, she did, she used to take me to church - to the - some - through the park, I know we used to go through the park, to a - a Scotch - church. And I us
ed to come back with her and I used to be - quite proud. Oh yes. It was just her way you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It would be the cook who sort of made sure you were going to church and got in on time if you were out and so on and not the mistress?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Oh no. No, you never saw the mistress.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there any of your jobs where the mistress took an interest in you personally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Not until the Rutlands, God bless 'em. They - they were good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were higher up then weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes I was, I was
 first kitchen maid then and - the children used to come in and - ask for carrots for their horses. And the father said, you're not to do it, you're not to worry Lucy. But I used to love doing it, they used to come in - slip in in the afternoon and say, c
o
uld they have a carrot for the horse. And then when I left, God bless her, the - Her Grace was at the back door with a horse, to say goodbye to me. And the Duke was always thanking me, if he saw me, for his barley water. He said I was the only one could m
ake his lemon barley. 'Cos he used to have a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that was the first time you really knew them as people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, as people, yes. Oh yes, the other ladies we never saw. Only - Lady - Lady Salisbury, we saw her - was at Christmas time, and
 she used to hand out - a length of material - to - make a new - print dress, for the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you could make your own dress out of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, you had to - get somebody to make it but - I mean, that's what we all got was a length.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were taught dressmaking though weren't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, in the school, but - but never had time. Never had time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They taught you accounts there did they as well, did they teach you book keeping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But you never used that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. Y
ou see - I went - cooking because that was the best thing out for me you see. But the school you mean. Lady Athelone. The Countess of - yes. Lady Athelone isn't it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Thinking about clothes, did the cook criticise the kind of clothes you wore when you went out in your own time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no. No. No, you could go out - dressed as you like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you never remember having remarks made about that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Or about the way you wore your hair in your own time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. I
 could - well we only had one way and that used to be bobbed. You see, you had bobbed - your - that was the fashion then. Short cut. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But they were pretty strict on what you wore during the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, as long as you had your - little bit o
f cap on. Little bit of lace. But - otherwise - long as you was clean they never - said anything you see. You'd have a clean apron perhaps every other day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And the cook would tell you off if you hadn't got a clean apron?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did you call the cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Madam. Madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What did she call you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Lucy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So it was always like that as scullery maid and as kitchen maid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, Lucy. Yes. Until you're made cook. Then they call you madam. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The mistress would call the cook Mrs so and so, is that right?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Even before you were married did that happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So when you were cooking at the Rutland's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, you always - would be - Mrs you see, you were never - well they used to ca
ll me Lucy, because they knew me - being from a kitchen maid you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they didn't do that to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No No. But the girls - like the - kitchen girls, it was always - I was madam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And when you were a scullery maid you called some of the men servants sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Which ones did you call sir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that would be the - valet, the butler, and then the - steward.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about footmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, you just call them their names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
hristian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Was there anywhere - none of these jobs there was a kind of common servants hall where the kitchen servants and the house servants met together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. We was always separate. Always separate. Never - never mixed with the - housemaids or footmen. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This contact with the children that you mentioned?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Ah well, they would come in the kitchen with the governess. She'd probably - just bring 'em down you know, and ask for something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you call them by their }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hristian names, the children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well Lady Ursula, Lady Isabelle, Lord Giles. And one incident there was - Lord Giles, he was only a boy of - six - and he said to my husband - which was - working at there at the time, we wasn't married, and he said - George can I have -
 he used to call me husband George, can I have - a box, hammer and nails? Naturally enough my husband got it for him. He wasn't long with this box, he started banging nails into it. So the governess, she got fed up. So she says, come along Giles, what are
 you going to make, table or a stable? Down went the tools. No more hammering there. And I say that to my children. I used to say it to them. I thought that was very good. Yes. What are you going to make, table or a stable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The second job you went to was Colonel Carslake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you did have some contact there with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh yes. Well that was with - I was being confirmed. At Southey Crescent. St Johns, Southwick Crescent, and our house - was facing that church. And of course -
 Lady Anne, she was being confirmed, and - and I was being confirmed too, so I was allowed to go - with the nanny across the road to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 For the classes you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, for the classes, and we were also - confirmed together. Which I was v
ery proud, to think I was with Lady Anne, although they was a very nice - family. Yes, very nice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So did that mean that they did take more interest you there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But I never saw no more of 'em, only at them times, you
 know. Never saw 'em through the week or anything. Only when it was time to go - over for our classes. Used to call to see - call down to the kitchen, to see if I was ready. But otherwise we were - never mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you dressed up in your best clothes for these classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes. In fact I had a coat - given to me belonged to - Miss Anne, Miss Kate. The younger one. The nanny gave me that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did that happen to you anywhere else that you were given coats like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, it was just them - but they give me a lovely coat of Miss Kate's. And I was proud to - you know, wearing that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long were you in that house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 About - ten months. Then I moved on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have a - they had a country house near Reading, Silchester?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You went there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they travel about anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, the - the - just the two houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was an active army man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A Colonel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he away a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, he was. Yes. And also they were training because - the war was still on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that meant there wasn't much entertaining going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no. And there - was where the - the water - to get our water, it didn't come through taps, like it does - do today, you
 had to pump it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This is in the countryside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. In the - that was fixed up in the scullery. You pumped your water, and - to get the hot water you had a copper, in the corner. So you used to - boil the hot water in this copper. And that's how t
hey got the baths, in the morning. A housemaid would come down - with a big can. And take it up. And there would be this round - zinc bath on a - the floor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that more primitive than you were used to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that's what they had them days you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They had that kind of thing in some of the other houses?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, oh yes. Yes them days. Yes that was a - natural thing. Like country houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They had bathrooms in the town houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In the town oh yes. There wasn't so bad but - in the country that's the sort of thing - you had to - be contented with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How large a staff was there at the Carslakes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was - ladies maid, a nanny }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 maid. A footman, we used to - hall boy, used to carry the trays - up to the nurse
ry, and clean the boots.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In the kitchen - there was the cook, and myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So this was a smaller place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes. Yes. Oh yes, we was - plenty to do. Oh yes, oh we did work hard but - if you were happy you didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was the next one the Harley Street doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's Doctor Mark Hovel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Hovel - Hovell. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What sort of size place was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well there there was - there was the cook, and myself, in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Two in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. And then there was a - housemaid and a between, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So just two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that was really quite simple?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, just a small job. But - I wanted to leave there. And I told the lady, 'cos she used to come dow
n - in the kitchen there every morning - and see the cook, and give - orders.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That wasn't usual in the places you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, not others but - that one it was see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You saw more of her really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes, every day. But I used to keep out the way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I used to go in the servants hall.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why did you do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - I - just you know, it was natural. While she was interviewing the - the cook you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you taught to keep out of sight then like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - natural - you - it came natural to you. So - and the war was on at that time and - used to have the boy scouts - used to go round and - on bicycles, with their bugles, lights out. And then all clear, they used to play.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were saying abo
ut she came down into the kitchen, then I think you were going to say something happened down there? You said you wanted to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, I wanted to leave. So - they - I had to give reason why I was leaving, and I told them, I wanted to - be a nurs
e. I've always wanted to be a nurse, up to even now. Yes. Yes. I doctor meself a lot now. So - they says, oh no, you can't be a nurse, you're too small. It was a shame because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you really applied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they put me off you see. She put me off. So I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you would have liked to have done war work really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But that's what I wanted to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You mean nursing the soldiers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Or nursing - in a hospital. See, I would have loved to have taken it up as a career. But as they said
, you know - that - I was too small - and another thing you had to have money behind you - them days. You couldn't go nursing like you can today. You had to have - parents with money behind you.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How did you hope that you would manage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I just thought I could you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you upset about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh certainly. Yes, from that day to this - I still wanted - to be a nurse, but then - being short I - forgot all about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This was an idea that came to you because you were working at the doctor's?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No doubt, no doubt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he have his surgery in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a nurse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, he had a nurse upstairs with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 But she didn't live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. She came in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What sort of patients did he have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Paid - patients, yes, it was a nose throat - surgeon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was quite a fashionable man was he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. But - he was very good.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they entertain much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - not a lot, no, they didn't 'cos of the war see. They had one boy and he was in a boarding school. We never saw much of - the boy.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did they have people to dinner parties?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Quite often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - once a week. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would be a less social life than the Countess of Connaught?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How often would you think she had something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh she - two or three times a week. See she was a different kind of woman - altogether to - Mrs Hovell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When you say that what exactly do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well - she was more quieter Mrs Hovell you know, more matured. Whereas the other one was more - I'm - the Countess and that's that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who was the Countess's husband, was he around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I couldn't tell you, I never had much to do with him. There. I couldn't say anything about him, 'cos I never had nothing -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He might have been somewhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Never heard much about him. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How long were you in Harley Street altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I should say - about eight months. It's still 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is that the last job before you went to the Cecil's? Did you go from Harley Street to the Cecils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes, 'cos I was still eighteen you see, when I went to Hatfield House, and - their place was in - Harley Street, by the Ritz Hotel, their London house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Arlington Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were two years there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. That's right.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's the one you told us most about I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I thought when we do the programme I'd like to talk about that house particularly, your time with the Cecils.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - what with the - oh, picallo - is that - tune - of the Copper House. Piccalo.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How does that go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Come down my copper hole. I don't want to come down your copper hole. I used to answer. Then he'd say, com
e down my copper hole. No, I don't want to come down your - copper hole, not me. And we used to have some laughs - about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that the place where the story about the meat coming between us, was that at the Cecils?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, that was in anothe
r job. The footman. Where - he - he - it appeared that the chef - being in the summer - the meat - was a little bit }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 taint}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
 it, you know, and the housemaids - oh they - was upset and said they couldn't eat it. So he come and put - the plates and meat and all that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you were saying that the meat came down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. And - of course you see - the - he said to me about it and I got - nasty, because - I felt awful. And he said all right, don't let the meat come between us. And I've always thought of that since. But - there was nothing I could do about it you see.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you really had a lot of fun at times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, I've always had - plenty of good - fun you know, here and there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Which do you think was the jolliest place that you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I say Rutlands. Yes, because you see, that's where I met me husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would make a difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You went out with a footman before?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - oh yes. Oh yes, that was at - a place called Roselea. In the Lake District, and
 - there - a gipsy came along. And she says - tell you your fortune my dear? I says, I could tell me own. But anyway, she insisted. And - she said - look - she says, the - the - the young man you're going out with now isn't for you. But when you go to you
r next place - you'll find your husband there. And it was funny - I did. So you see they do tell fortunes - true.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So who did Roselea belong to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 To Rutlands.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who was your employer at Roselea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh no, that wasn't - was it - Hill. The name of Hill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That would be after Mrs Verily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You had so many different places.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Let's see. Yes. And we haven't - introduced the Mansion House have we?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can I ask you about Roseleas, this was their summer house was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - Roselea - is - the Rutland's - another country house. Yes. And then from there you go on - to Beavor Castle. See we done a lot of travelling them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you were already employed by the Duchess there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, you was always - trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many houses did the Rutlands have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well there was Abnor Hall. Bakewell. And - that was where - Dorothy Vern - sloped. And - we also - used to have our - afternoons off at - we didn't have nowhere to go. Used to just walk around and - 
and then back again. Then go to our bedroom, and stay there - for the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they moved from one house to another at different times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you went with them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, that's right, the kitchen staff - always went with them you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So they knew they were getting good food always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 From the Cecils you went to the Mansion House, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's one of the biggest establishments you were in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that was
 - Lord Mayors. And I saw two Lord Mayors. I was veg cook there, and I used to have - forty dishes - of spinach, forty dishes of - potatoes, and peas and all that sort of thing. And used to put it into a - hot cupboards. That used to keep it - all hot and
 
as the courses - came along, so I used to - hand this out, on the tray. But one thing happened there was - the - I had a good laugh and I think the other staff did, the - it was - the Passover, the Jewish Passover, and of course - they saw - the - Rabbi c
o
ming down the steps, and they says, oh dear, we've got the chickens on and he hasn't blessed 'em, so they took 'em off quick and put 'em on a - on a tray, enamel tray, and - the Rabbi blessed 'em, and then they put 'em back. We all laughed - the way it wa
s done so quick.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was there a Jewish Lord Mayor at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Rolls I think his name was. I saw two in there. One in and one out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Who was the other one you saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well that I don't - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You never saw them really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were there sort of permanent officials and so on in the Mansion House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. You see, there was a police station there. Yes. As you go in the door there's a police station, you know, cells, wh
ere they lock 'em up. Oh yes, as you go in the door. Yes, and then of course we used to go - a long corridor, before we got into our kitchen. Well then there'd only be - four of us working in the kitchen, ordinary. There'd be a scullery maid and a - veg m
a
id, myself, and the second - kitchen maid, like used to do all the - secretaries trays, cooked for the - the staff. She used to - like the meat and - sweet and all that for the staff, and then there was a - a lady cook, but she was - chef trained, her hus
band was a chef. Oh yes, she was a chef trained but when all these big does were on, we had two or three - chefs come in.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They came in specially did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, just for the - occasion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And quite a lot of waiters and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. But
lers and valets, and they used to - line up - from the kitchen door - up to the - banquet hall, oh it - it - used to be wonderful, to see them passing - the things from the - cold - dishes - from the pantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Very skilled you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes, that'd be their evening off I expect. They'd come from other jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They were earning extra wages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that really you did produce big meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, we did. Oh yes. Oh yes, we worked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 hard - when it was - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did you sleep in that place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 At the top of the house. At the top.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was always at the top was it wherever you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 More or less, yes. Oh yes, more or less was the top - of the house. Used to share a room.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that the first time you were the vegetable cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, that was me first}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 time that I - took on just - vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that was quite a step forward?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, it was. Yes, and I got that from Jackson's, that position. Recommended by a chef.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You never used an agency called Massey's did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Is there anything else about the Mansion House?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, that's all there is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You were there about a year and a half?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Then it was Sir Marcus Samuel you went to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, in - Park Lane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Can you tell me a little bit about him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - they were very nice people, they were Jewish. But - we used to go to Maidstone - a place called the Moat, and there - in the grounds is where there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s a train - runs through a
nd that's the only one - that goes through the grounds, even now. And - we used to have our days out there. So - and they used to have - grooms there. And - the footmen - used to dress up - in - tights, stockings and - cockade hats, and - horse and pair, 
and that's how they used to go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was rather more elaborate that was usual wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes Yes. But every Christmas - the br}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 other of Lord Samuels - Marquis}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  of Samuels, he - used to give - everybody he'd pass a pound. On the estate.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 A generous man then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. He was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Going back to this carriage, did you call them postillions, or footmen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Footmen. Footmen, they were footmen, the first and second footmen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So do you think he was trying to put on a show rather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well it - was natural you see. But it - I think they did do it them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I thought you felt this was rather more of a show than was usual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - yes, to - what to see the footmen behind. Oh yes, in this carriage, and them sitting in the - carri
age, you know, and the - driver, he was dressed in the uniform too, the coachman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why do you think though that he had much more sort of elaborate uniforms and so on than most of the people that you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I - I think - you see, to be a
 Lord Mayor - I've always been under that impression - that you had to have a lot of money. You - you've got to be a moneyed man. But you mustn't be - anything - like - only just a citizen, you couldn't be - Lord this and Lo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 rd that. They called him Marqui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s of Salisbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 This is Sir Marcus Samuel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 Samuel. Yes. Samuel. Marqui}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 s of Samuel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So you feel he was unusually rich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh he was rich. Oh yes, he was rich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he do a lot of entertaining down in the country?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about in the country though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And he did sho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ting. And fishing. In the moat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 In his own moat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes -.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was he just like a country gentleman when he was down there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You didn't notice any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh he done a lot of - entertaining, you know, like shooting and all that sort of thing. But - we never - met them. Not the kitchen. No, no, Used to have big dinners, and they did cricket. Oh I remembered us - getting ready for the cricket. At - Kent
 - cricket. We used to provide the - picnics for 'em. Such as - sandwiches and - coffee, tea. Used to provide all that, from the kitchen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 When people came to stay in the house like that they would bring their own servants would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. They used to bring their ladies maid with 'em. And the gentlemen would bring his - valet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You wouldn't meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No, because - they had their own - hall. Which you - you know, they'd go with this - butler. The butler never mixed - with the other}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 staff. He was always - with the ladies maid and the housekeeper. And the cook.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
I've heard it said that when people came to visit like that they used to regard the servants who came from the bigger household as more important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You remember that kind of discussion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes, you - you'd hear like the other servants talk. About who's here and who isn't here, you know. But otherwise we never met them.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That didn't affect the kitchen so much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No. No. No, never - never - affected the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you feel more proud if you were in service yourself with the Salisbury for instance than you would if you were with Sir Marcus Samuel?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well I don't think that we - made any difference, I know I had to work hard. There w
as always plenty of work, like such as - you - your vegetables there, although they're only carrots, onions and potatoes, but - you used to have to have - done so many different ways - that - it made the - vegetables a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I notice you've been in som
e very big households and some much smaller ones, I just wondered whether you felt sometimes you went into a household because it was a big one and that was one of the attractions, that this was a big place, you know, it's like almost a step up to move in
to a bigger household?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh certainly. Oh yes, and more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They paid better did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well, they paid a bit more than the others you see. You never got much. It'd only be two and six. That's all. But still - your money was going up as you went along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many servants did Sir Marcus Samuel have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Well - she had a - ladies maid and he had a - butler valet. And he had a first footman, which was very good. And then he had - a second and - hall boy. Pantry boy. Used to - carry all t
he trays up to the dining room you know, when the big dinners were on. He used to - that was his job, carrying the - trays up and bringing down the empties, to the - scullery, and the silver into the pantry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 There was - there - there was the cook. Kitchen maid and myself. Three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So that's sort of middle sized by your experience?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes, it was. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Do you remember how long you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Six months I - about six months. I know - I was taken
 ill - when I give me month's notice, well that epidemic flu was on, very bad flu, and I was in bed chiefly - my month's notice, I didn't know how to face the poor cook - when it come to time to go, because I'd been in bed. And I'd had a lovely doctor. He
r ladyship had - he - he used to come and see me. Was well looked after. But honest I - didn't know how to face the poor cook. But of course you see, she'd got another kitchen maid and I - had got me job so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You decided to leave?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And you went to Mrs Bailey was it from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's where I went, yes, Bailey. Yes. South Horley Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 South Audley Street?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And she also had Lake House in Wiltshire?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well she rented that you see. Rented that you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How much of the year did she spend there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 They - they used to have about - three months you see, and three months in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What was her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was a - MP. Yes. For - Stockport. Up near - near New Mills.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Lancashire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How large a place was that then, the number of servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
There was just the footman and the housemaid. And - between. And - cook, she was chef trained, and myself. And I know - that - while I was there - the - cook got cross one day, what hap
pened - it was the fish kettle as they call it them days - a oblong saucepan that they used to cook the fish in. And she got so mad that she threw it all across the kitchen at me. But lucky it missed me. Kettle fish of hot water.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Why did she do that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She accused me of having - to put - sacks - at the top of the oven so it shouldn't draw up. Shouldn't burn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So did you decide to leave after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Definitely because I wasn't used to that sort of thing. Not that treatment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 So how long were you with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh only a few months. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did you go from there to the Rutlands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Where did I go to? It was - would be, yes, 'cos that was - I was getting on for twenty then wasn't I? Yes, it would be the Rutlands.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 How many years were you with the Rutlands?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
I think I was there two years. Yes, well I - I wanted to make up - and be - a cook, which I - that was my ambition. My ambition was to be a cook, before I got married. So - as - there's a chef and he left. And then w
e had a woman cook. But God bless the poor soul, she'd only been used to - one gentleman. When it come to having all these shooting parties, and all that sort of thing, she didn't know much - know much about it. And when she left - they give me - the chan
ce of being cook. Although I wasn't cook very long. 'Cos I was young you see twenty-six.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And that was a big place wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. There was all these - shooting parties to get ready, to send out - the - you know, the - all the food. Besides a
ll these big dinners they had. At night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Roughly how many people were there there, the staff?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The staff - was - now there was - the steward. The butler. The valet. And there was the ladies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 maid. Housekeeper, and the cook. They all shared - a roo
m on their own for meals. But then there was seven housemaids. It was - four - footmen. And a pantry boy. And then there was us four - in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It's a lot isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And a groom of chambers I seem to remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh - but ther
e was a lot but still - so we never went in the hall - but - I know the Duke, when he came to - Christmas, instead of giving us - a present each, he - had a film - of Charlie Chaplin. And we all went in - to this film, from the estate, and I think there w
a
s about - nearly a hundred because there was the - postmen and the firemen. 'Cos they - they had their cottages on the at - at the gates. And there was laundry maids. Still room maids. Had a still room. So the kitchen never did toast. Never made no scones
, no cakes. Nothing of that. Tea, coffee - all came from the stillroom. And there was two in there. Then there was all the boffies, gardeners, dairy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It's like a little town really isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 It was, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's when your husband appears in the story isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You did tell me quite a lot about that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was groom of chambers what they call - he had his own little office}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 -}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 box room. And there he had the switchboard. And he'd see the post in and out, he was responsible f
or all that, and he was responsible for the - gamekeepers, counting the pheasants, and the partridges and rabbits and - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Was that because they were worried that some of them might disappear on the side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well they - you see, I think they used to sell them. See, they used to sell 'em as well - keep so many - for the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Were you ever allowed in the k}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 itchen to sort of sell off left}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 overs and this sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 The only thing we were allowed was - when I was a scu
llery maid - I used to - well at least the scullery maid there did, rabbit skins - and the - pheasant feathers, the - the tail - used to get so much for them. And of course the cook, she got dripping money. Tuppence a pound, and the - there was - they use
d to come in, you know, and ask you - if you're still dripping. Oh we - we - you know, you could get fun out of the places. Even if you are hard worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You certainly seem to have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Going back to your husband I think you said that he had training in shorthand? In Belfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Oh, he went - he was Pitmans. His - grandmother - she wanted him to be - in the mill, work in the mill, and - you know, from - work from a boy upwards. Well he didn't like that. He couldn't see that. And
 yet - it was the best way to know how to run a mill. So he left - and came to - England. And he went to the - Whiteley's. And he saw Mr Whiteley, and he took to him. But of course he wanted him to sleep in, and my husband didn't want to sleep in. So he t
u
rned him down. But he went as a hatter, in - what's his - hat shops. Where they do hats you know, to serve hats. Anyway, he - they always came to him because he knew - how to - fit a hat. He used to get the hot iron and - put over it and - fit it on the g
entleman's head and - they always were satisfied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He had very different talents then didn't he?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he become a soldier at one point?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Then he went - in the Army. And he went out to India. On the police. And - he came back - 
and - then he went in the first world war. Went to the Battle of - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 Gallipoli}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
, and - they had to run away quick. So he said they had to destroy all the - horses. And - and went through - the night, onto the boat. And went to the - the Battle of Somme. France. And that's where he got wounded. He was on the guns.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he come back from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
From there he came back wounded. And he went to - up to - the North. A hospital there. And then of course - he - from there he - he came to - England. He got tw
o pound a week pension. And then they said - after a long while - from two pound they gave him eight shillings. Said he had passed away. But he never accepted it. And he never accepted his medals. 'Til he went up to the British Legion - when he start gett
ing heart attacks, and they said about we've got your medals. And - after we'd - left - our post and went to live you know as - ordinary - we got a flat - furnished, in Fernhead Road, and of course he - while he was waiting to go to Whitehall -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That's where he was a clerk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
Yes. We - he took up a post - for Ringer Primers, painting. And - of course we hadn't got no - painters overall, or brushes. So the only thing we could do was to pawn the medals. And all they'd give us was two and six on the medal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Bad times then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes, it was bad times. But we got over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 I was interested to hear that he was prepared to do painting, because I thought one of the problems was that he didn't in fact like doing -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 No, he didn't like - oh - you d
on't mean Creasy's job. Oh that was - Mrs Christy, that was when we left Rutlands. We took up Aga - Agatha Christy, and of course - we got married in - Christchurch, East Greenwich, Registrar, because we only had a - two week's, to take up our post. And -
 
of course - we - we went in and - all there was - after us having a big staff, it was a come down I'll admit. There was only a betweeny, and a wife - of the gardener that used to come in. Myself. And there was a - nursemaid, she had for her daughter. But 
s
he didn't help with the chores. We had a betweeny. And of course - she was always giving these parties. You know, tea parties and dinners. For twelve. And poor me, I used to have to do the cooking and me own washing up. And he used to have to do the waiti
n
g, and the washing up. But I used to have to go and give him a hand too. And - he used to get so cross - that he got hold of the - finger bowls and three 'em in the cupboard. And one got broken. So next time there was a dinner - he put eleven out, he laid
 
eleven finger bowls up, and left - Mrs Christy with none. Well - he said - she can't say nothing to me while there's a - a dinner on. We always laugh about that. She couldn't say anything to him while there was a dinner on. So - the next day she said, wha
t happened to the finger bowl. Well he said, I'm sorry madam it got broken.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 If you'd like to tell us that story on Tuesday I think that's a very good one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What about the polish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh and then of course - he was asked to do 
the dining room. And - that was on our half day out. So - he just - put a bit here and a bit there, and left it. And when - Mrs Christy came down and - looked round, just saw this polish, she had to get the - gardener's wife - to do it. And Colonel Christ
y came in in the evening and he says, this looks lovely. So me husband, he just give a smile. He didn't say what had happened. Well, he said, he wasn't used to that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He was a skilled man really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Certainly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 He felt they were tr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid416815\charrsid6044787 y}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 ing to be a bit above themselves, the Christie's with these dinners and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 She's still alive. I'll leave that there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 You went on from there, you had this nice time with Mr Enson which you told me about, then to the school rather briefly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Oh yes. Well then of course - we - we went to Mr Henderson, we went as - caretakers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That was a nice job. And he was a very nice gentleman.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And then very briefly the Ham Common school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And then we - from t
here - I found I was pregnant. So - we had to leave Mr Henderson. Which he was very upset. But - we got this here school - post and - at Ham Common, but oh - oh dear, it didn't suit me husband. The boys - that he had working for him - was only young boys 
h
ere - fifteen. And - they used to throw the - blancmange up the ceiling. Oh dear, dear, so of course me husband gave that job up. But they couldn't turn me out the cottage, because - although he had to go and see the Justice of Peace - because I wasn't fi
t - to leave the cottage. And then we went to Surbiton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 And then there was the last job, Colonel Grimson?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 What happened there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Well, we went to - we got this here post. At - up in - it's a place -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Chipping Sodbury?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 That
's right, Chipping Sodbury, and - when we got there - we found there was no - no room. And we was supposed to have a room. The - room was - over - a - kitchen. And our furniture would never have gone into it. Then apart from that - we - we couldn't take u
p
 our post, which we were supposed to do, because there was no - he hadn't got nowhere to go. So - he asked my husband to do - gardening, sawing up wood. And my husband refused. And he said, you refuse? He said, yes. He says - I was - employed here as a bu
tler. Not a - a - gardener. So he says - I'll sue you. 'Cos my husband give notice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3022891 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 Did he sue him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12593098 LM  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787 
So my husband - said, all right. So he called the - gardener. He said, make that statement. And he says, you asked me to saw wood, which isn't my job, and I refused. So he went to - his solicitors, in Bath, and we went to Tippy, Lon}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid15410870\charrsid6044787 g and Vale, in Bath. And we won}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9964653\charrsid6044787  the day. He - Colonel, Brent, he had to send the furniture back to London. And - there was our month's wages.

